Position Summary
The Department of Epidemiology at the Mailman School of Public Health is seeking an experienced Data Analyst to conduct quantitative analyses for two NIH-funded projects. The first project is entitled Community- and school-level policing, School Discipline, and Student Health Outcomes: Identifying the Adolescent Health Consequences of Racialized Criminalization and Securitization in New York City Schools. This project involves psychiatric and substance use epidemiology with a specific focus on adolescent health and mass criminalization and incarceration. The second project is entitled Substance Use Treatment and County Incarceration (STACI). This project examines how community-level exposure to mass incarceration can contribute to county substance use disorder treatment needs and affect treatment availability, use, and outcomes. A candidate with an interest in areas of health related to these projects is preferred. The successful candidate will have excellent written and oral communication skills, strong interpersonal and organizational skills, and attention to detail. Experience with managing large data frames, multi-level and longitudinal data analysis, and data visualization is critical.
This position will work with the principal investigators and other investigators to:
Conduct data acquisition, processing/cleaning, and linkages
Perform quantitative multivariate analyses to fulfill research aims
Conduct latent variable analysis and linear modeling
Contribute (as a co-author) to reports, manuscripts, figures, tables, slides, and other presentation materials based on study findings
Contribute to new and ongoing grant proposals as needed
Individuals from groups historically underrepresented in health-related research are strongly encouraged to apply. The position also has the potential to work in a similar capacity on the principal investigator’s other research projects.
Responsibilities
Conduct data acquisition, processing/coding, and linkages 35%
Conduct data analysis to fulfill research aims - 50%
Write and edit research manuscripts, slides, and other materials - 10%
Perform other related duties & responsibilities as assigned/requested 5%
Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor's degree, plus three years of experience.
Preferred Qualifications
The candidate must have a master’s degree or equivalent in training, education, and/or experience in the fields of statistics or biostatistics. Proficiency in R and experience working with quantitative data management and analysis are essential.
Work experience in psychiatric or substance use epidemiology is preferred. Experience with STATA and ArcGIS is preferred. Interest in adolescent mental health, substance use treatment across the life course, and mass criminalization and incarceration is preferred.

Equal Opportunity Employer / Disability / Veteran

JOB OBJECTIVE:
The Senior Data Coordinator develops and performs data vendor analyses for the purpose of maximizing the utilization of data in the portal, underwriting analysis, data warehouse, and predictive analytics. Utilizing industry standard tools to establish underwriting dashboard for the purpose of capturing and showing data at an account level. Develops and assists in the implementation of new business requirements for new products, systems, and rules. Ensures data collection, utilization and storage meet regulatory compliance requirements. This position works collaboratively with but not limited to CL small business Regional Vice Presidents, IT, compliance, legal, supply management services, portal team, and actuary. This position will coach, train and mentor strategic business unit staff and other staff on guidelines, standards, and other technical aspects specific to data management, integration, contacts and utilization of data. This position will be responsible for the data vendor budget, cost/benefit analysis, and maximizing the utilization of data. This position will work with legal to draft and review data contracts specially as they pertain to estimated utilization, service level agreements, selection of data elements and penalties.

2. Collaboratively manage and lead data projects – including business requirements and timelines – that impact process, procedure and practices related to the use of data or data integrations.
3. Work with legal to draft and review data contracts especially as they pertain to estimated utilization, service level agreements, selection of data elements and penalties.

8. Establish and maintain data vendor relationships to identify new innovations and improve negotiations.
9. Identify and determine the appropriate data elements to purchase to maximize customer satisfaction, minimize cost and reduce loss ratio.
10. Develop tools to manage and reduce agency gaming and producer input errors.
11. Collaborate with data management team to improve the utilization of data in reports.

We are actively seeking a Data Analyst with a minimum of 16 years' experience. This opportunity is supporting the customer’s enterprise data analytics group working closely with Sponsor leadership to develop and maintain a security and governance approach for multi-tenancy on the Splunk SOAR platform. Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree are preferred in one or more discipline but can be waived if previous direct support to this customer’s agency. Specific skills include the following:
Experience working with IT enterprise data (desktops, servers, network devices, and applications) to determine issues
Experience utilizing and configuring key performance indicators (KPIs) and glass tables using Splunk IT Service Intelligence (ITSI)
Experience briefing external customers as well as sponsor leadership on data analysis as it correlates with network performance
Working with various cloud and on premises system configurations
Working within various ticketing systems to track work and log potential threats and issues (eg; JIRA, ServiceNow)

Preferred Education, Experience, & Skills
Splunk certification
Strong background with Splunk Enterprise and Splunk Enterprise Security
Ability to interpret, modify, and create scripts using Python or Shell

Pay Information
Full-Time Salary Range: $147300 - $250400

Please note: This range is based on our market pay structures. However, individual salaries are determined by a variety of factors including, but not limited to: business considerations, local market conditions, and internal equity, as well as candidate qualifications, such as skills, education, and experience.

Employee Benefits: At BAE Systems, we support our employees in all aspects of their life, including their health and financial well-being. Regular employees scheduled to work 20+ hours per week are offered: health, dental, and vision insurance; health savings accounts; a 401(k) savings plan; disability coverage; and life and accident insurance. We also have an employee assistance program, a legal plan, and other perks including discounts on things like home, auto, and pet insurance. Our leave programs include paid time off, paid holidays, as well as other types of leave, including paid parental, military, bereavement, and any applicable federal and state sick leave. Employees may participate in the company recognition program to receive monetary or non-monetary recognition awards. Other incentives may be available based on position level and/or job specifics.

About BAE Systems Intelligence & Security
BAE Systems, Inc. is the U.S. subsidiary of BAE Systems plc, an international defense, aerospace and security company which delivers a full range of products and services for air, land and naval forces, as well as advanced electronics, security, information technology solutions and customer support services. Improving the future and protecting lives is an ambitious mission, but it’s what we do at BAE Systems. Working here means using your passion and ingenuity where it counts – defending national security with breakthrough technology, superior products, and intelligence solutions. As you develop the latest technology and defend national security, you will continually hone your skills on a team—making a big impact on a global scale. At BAE Systems, you’ll find a rewarding career that truly makes a difference. Intelligence & Security (I&S), based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do—from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels. At BAE Systems, we celebrate the array of skills, experiences, and perspectives our employees bring to the table. For us, differences are a source of strength. We’re laser-focused on high performance, and we work hard every day to nurture an inclusive culture where all employees can innovate and thrive. Here, you will not only build your career, but you will also enjoy work-life balance, uncover new experiences, and collaborate with passionate colleagues.

description:
Description:
Are you excited about a new opportunity? Do you have a passion for providing high quality patient support? Are you mission-driven to help improve health and eliminate inequities in health outcomes in under-resourced communities in DC? Well, look no further! At Community of Hope, we have worked diligently to improve health and end family homelessness to make Washington, DC, more equitable. We believe everyone in DC should have access to good healthcare, a stable income, and home, and hope! If you are ready to make a positive difference in the community, this position is for you!
At COH, we strive for: Caring for Families. Improving Lives. Leading Change
Our Approach and Values:
We care for families by providing direct services with a focus on prevention, healing, and wellness.
We improve lives by building on families’ strengths, honoring their choices, and taking a whole-family, multi-generational approach.
We lead and advocate for system change to address the effects of historical and current racial inequities on health outcomes and housing opportunities.
We embrace the diversity of our community, welcome all voices and perspectives, and treat everyone with respect, compassion, and integrity.
We strive for excellence in all that we do, implement evidence-based practices, measure our outcomes, and use this knowledge to continuously strengthen our work.
Position Summary: The Data Analyst, Population Health provides data analysis to support Population Health program management, Population Health staff accountability, and accurate reporting of data to funders and other stakeholders. Additionally, the Data Analyst will participate in quality improvement initiatives by creating accurate Population Health & Hospital Utilization data analyses, reports and dashboards for the Population Health team, to ensure high quality of care for patients and clients.
The pay rate for this position ranges between $28.84 - $31.25 per hour and the offer amount is determined by the candidate's education, qualifications, and experience . Indeed provides their own estimated salary calculator and is not affiliated with COH's range.
Highlighted Duties and Responsibilities:
Participates in the development of the Quality Improvement (QI) Plan in collaboration with the QI team and population health team annually.
Completes data analysis and data visualization using Excel, SQL coding in Relevant, and external data from insurance partners & hospital systems for external grant reporting & participation in value-based contracts / quality incentive programs.
Provides data as needed to support internal Population Health quality improvement work.
Works with site-based leadership teams & Quality Improvement working groups to advance process improvement work related to expanding and improving care management and reducing hospitalizations.
Participates in staff meetings and provides data & process updates on Continuous Quality Improvement (CQI) activities, as well as performance updates monthly.
Supports CQI activities, primarily through consistent provision of accurate data & collaboration with population health leadership and staff to improve documentation, and quality of care.
Completes regular quality assurance activities that support the population health team’s processes.
Participates in external learning opportunities such as the Relevant Users Group, DCPCA Quality Improvement Peer Learning Collaborative, Value Based Care learning collaboratives, as directed.
Supports Director of Care Management, Associate Director of Care Management, and Population Health Program Mmanagers and leads (Community Health Workers, Refugee Health, My Health GPS, Nutrition, etc.) to create eCW templates to capture data so that information can be easily and accurately gathered and analyzed.
Remains up to date with health information software and platforms including but not limited to eCW Relevant, Excel, CRS Reporting Suite, Availity, Arcadia, and other population health platforms as needed.
Works with eCW Specialist to ensure the EHR contains the necessary modifications and build outs to meet clinical and staff needs.
Collaborates with other QI team data analysts and COH Data Hub analysts to interpret & communicate external hospitalization data, improve documentation and health outcomes for HEDIS measures and hospitalization metrics such as hospital readmissions, potentially preventable admissions, and non-emergent ED visits. .
Creates and completes accurate reports and dashboards for grant funded population health expansion projects, quality improvement committee meetings, site health leadership meetings and more.
Provides key clinical information for fundraising and communications purposes as needed.
Performs other duties as requested by supervisor.*
Requirements:
Minimum Qualifications:
Bachelor's Degree required, Master’s (MPH or similar) degree preferred.
Knowledge of primary care and health maintenance required.
Experience with eClinicalWorks or other EHR preferred.
Advanced Microsoft Excel required.
Advanced SQL coding skills required
Experience extracting and analyzing health data required.
Strong data visualization skills preferred
Strong organizational skills with an ability to multitask and work with teams.
Ability to see complex projects through to completion.
Commitment to work with under resourced populations.
Ability to travel to different sites at Community of Hope required.
Ability to work in a non-profit environment.
Proof of required vaccinations is required. This includes, but may not be limited to, Flu and Covid. COH will consider requests for reasonable accommodations for anyone who cannot be vaccinated for a religious or medical reason, subject to applicable law.
In relation to remote work versus on-site expectations, this position is classified as the following: Hybrid: Remote work and on-site work requirements are generally split roughly 50/50. Please note that remote work designations are subject to change or fluctuate at any point in time and the supervisor may require in person learning for a specific amount of time after hire.
At COH, we understand the toll that the Covid-19 pandemic has taken on the workforce, which is why we prioritize the following well-being and work-life balance-centered benefits:
Remote work opportunities are available for many of our roles, promoting a culture of work-life balance.
8-hour workdays, which include a paid lunch
11.5 paid company holidays, 1 personal floating holiday, 15 days of paid vacation (increases to 20 after 3 years of service), and 12 days of paid sick leave on an annual basis
Annual performance-based raises, up to 5% of your annual pay
National Health Service Corps (NHSC) and DC Health Professional Loan Repayment Program (DCHPLRP) participants
Tuition reimbursement, loan repayment for clinicians, licensing reimbursement, and continuing education unit funds for licensed staff
Many opportunities for internal promotions and transfers across the agency as we continue to grow; we average 30+ promotions each year
Ongoing internal leadership training for supervisors
Diversity, equity, and inclusion training and initiatives for all staff
Ongoing well-being activities, culture compact activities, and trauma-informed care initiatives
Medical/Dental/Vision Plans through CareFirst BlueCross Blue Shield
Life insurance, short-term disability, and long-term disability insurance
403(b) Retirement Plan
Flexible Spending Accounts for medical and dependent care reimbursable expenses
And much more!
About Us:
Community of Hope is a mission-driven, innovative, and rapidly growing nonprofit. For over 40 years, we have provided healthcare, housing, and supportive services for under-resourced, underserved and people experiencing homelessness in Washington, DC. As a Federally Qualified Health Center, we provide medical, dental, emotional wellness, and care coordination services for the whole family at three locations in DC. Community of Hope also strongly emphasizes maternal and child health, with midwifery practice and the only free-standing birth center in DC. In 2020, Community of Hope provided about 28,400 medical visits, 7,000 dental visits, and 10,000 behavioral health visits for about 11,000 patients. Community of Hope provides community walk-in COVID testing and COVID vaccines. Community of Hope is also one of the largest providers in DC of housing and support services for families and individuals experiencing homelessness. Through providing these programs, we live out our mission to improve health and end family and individual homelessness to make Washington, DC, more equitable.
We were selected as one of The Washington Post 150 Top Workplaces in 2024 and 6 other times since 2014 based on feedback from our staff.
To request a reasonable accommodation to complete an employment application or for general questions about employment with Community of Hope, contact a Recruiting Coordinator. Email: hr@cohdc.org Phone: 202-407-7747. Community of Hope is an equal opportunity employer.

Why it’s worth it:

As a Senior Data Analyst at ReliaQuest, you will be on the front line of building systems and deriving insight that drives RQ and our customers’ businesses forward. You will make a tangible difference in the understanding and practice of cybersecurity, visibility into threats and customer systems, and the fast-paced innovation of RQ.

You will be a technical and thought leader on how to best build insights and the systems used to generate them. Business as usual is not something you’ll see here, and we maintain a culture of innovation. You will bring a strong skillset in some of our most used tools: Snowflake, Power BI, dbt, GitLab, Python, and SQL. You’ll put these tools to good use in developing predictive models and analytics, designing and delivering information that excels in good storytelling, and generating impactful information for customers and your RQ colleagues. And you’ll do all this working in collaborative, high-performing teams.

The everyday hustle:

Developing complex data analyses, methodologies, and predictive data models that provide visibility and insight into both ReliaQuest and customer operations
Leading innovative projects that include a variety of advanced qualitative and quantitative analytic assignments

Providing relevant data-related reports and insights to customers, partners, executives, and ReliaQuest colleagues

Excellent visual design skills
Experience leading projects to completion
Excellent written and oral communication skills including an ability to communicate with internal and external cross functional teams (technical and business)
Strong attention to detail
Great attitude, energy and effort

Graduate degree in Management Information Systems, Business Administration and Management, Business Analytics and Information Systems, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Physics, Economics or a similar degree
Prior experience in cybersecurity analysis
Goes above and beyond and continuously learns new skills
Experience building systems for data

About the Role
The Data Analyst is responsible for enhancing the organization’s decision-making by developing and maintaining high-quality reports and dashboards. Key duties include setting up and managing the data hub, creating tailored reports for various departments, and ensuring timely and accurate data exchange with stakeholders. The analyst performs in-depth analysis of business performance metrics like revenue, profitability, and client retention, and prepares accurate commission and bonus submissions. Additionally, they contribute to the setup and testing of new data and analytics platforms, providing actionable insights through rigorous data validation and analysis. The role requires collaboration with users to deliver impactful dashboards and reports, supporting data-driven decisions and identifying emerging trends.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities
Set up and maintain reports and dashboards in the data hub utilizing best practices for data visualization to improve the overall quality and impact of dashboards.
Define, manage, and execute projects to create appropriate reports for each department
Engage with single or multiple stakeholders to ensure timely quality and well-communicated data exchange is achieved.
Build and maintain data hub, new reports, and ad hoc reports for various business crucial KPIs
Perform analysis on business performance metrics (revenue, profitability, client retention, employee productivity, etc.)
Prepare important, timely, and accurate commission and bonus submissions for the organization based on data from various systems on a daily, weekly, and monthly basis for review by various stakeholders
Develop reports and dashboards for use across the organization, collecting feedback and partnering with users to understand and deliver usable information.
Participate in setting up and testing a new data and analytics platform.
Synthesize current business trend data to support recommendations for action.
Provide analytical support by creating reports and applications to drive data-driven decision-making.
Validate posted commission reports from carriers and develop detailed producer commission reports.
Ensure data accuracy, consistency, and reliability by employing rigorous testing and validation methods
Provide expert insights on data VA.
Uses data analysis and interpretation to develop conclusions, make recommendations, support decision-making, and identify trends and emerging issues.
Desired Outcomes
Improvement in data-driven decision-making- enhance the organization's decision-making process by delivering accurate and insightful reports and dashboards, enabling various departments to make informed business decisions.
Efficiency in Reporting and Dashboard Management: Establish and maintain a streamlined process for generating reports and dashboards, ensuring that data is presented in a clear, timely, and impactfully, particularly for business-critical KPIs.
Accurate and Timely Commission Reporting: Ensure the accuracy and timeliness of commission and bonus submissions by developing and maintaining detailed reports from various systems, directly supporting financial operations and stakeholder reviews.
Identification of Business Trends and Opportunities: Analyze business performance metrics to identify patterns, trends, and opportunities for improvement, supporting strategic initiatives and providing actionable recommendations
Data Accuracy and Consistency: Maintain a high standard of data accuracy, consistency, and reliability by employing rigorous testing, validation methods, and continuous monitoring, contributing to the overall integrity of the organization’s data infrastructure.
Employment & Educational Experience
Minimum
3-5 years of experience in corporate financial data analysis, modeling, and reporting.
Proven ability to analyze data and discover trends.
Proficient in SQL, Excel, and QuickBooks.
Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Computer Information Systems, Management Information Systems, Finance, Statistics, Business Analytics or related field.
Preferred
3-5 years of experience in corporate financial data analysis, modeling, and reporting in the Insurance Industry.
Programming experience in Python preferred.
Master’s degree in any of the fields listed above.

description:
Position Description
This is a fully benefited, full-time Harvard University position that has been funded through December 31, 2025. There is the possibility of renewal, contingent on funding, university priorities and satisfactory job performance.

The Administrative Data Management and Reporting Ecosystem (ADMIRE) project is designed to create a comprehensive data strategy that enables the institution to leverage administrative data to inform decisions, make predictions, and otherwise understand our operations. The demand for high-quality, normalized, and interconnected data has continued to increase, with the emergence of generative artificial intelligence putting a spotlight on the challenges of data quality and data governance. This project prioritizes the foundational technology and related services that will enable such initiatives to move forward easily in the future. The ADMIRE project will enable us to leverage the full value of our digital assets for an enterprise-wide approach to data governance, create a modern data ecosystem, and incorporate best practices into our data management capabilities.

We are looking for an experienced data analyst and modeler with a curious mind who can work with different SMEs and develop design artifacts. This person will play an integral role in the data architecture practice and upcoming data governance practice. This is an exciting role to have an opportunity to develop the data blueprint for the Harvard University Data ecosystem.

Principal Duties and Responsibilities:

A curious minded, people savvy data analyst to work in the Reporting Analytics and Integrated Data team to deliver high quality data analysis to building new data warehouses and delivering analytical projects. This is an individual contributor role. The principal responsibilities are to:
Produce data models using Erwin or ERStudio & artifacts in the IDMC data governance application (training will be provided, candidate is expected to understand the fundamentals of data governance principles)
Assess the source system process and data to set up data interfaces
Work with SMEs to understand data requirements
Provide input to data design
Articulate findings and present models
Understand data modeling for transaction systems (3rd normal forms) and datawarehouses (star schemas, snapshots)
The role will perform the following functions:
Manage aspects of data management services which may include database and analytics platform research and design, database performance and optimization, recovery/load strategy and implementation, and data modeling
Assist with the preparation of data verification and testing methods for data/applications loaded into the warehouse, or other data repositories, to ensure compatibility across different sources
Code, develop, and document scripts and stored procedures
Collaborate with stakeholders to prepare data acquisition/access analysis
Provide technical expertise and direction in developing and supporting system level programs & documentation for specific systems and processes
Troubleshoot advanced problems and recommend appropriate action
May provide training to clients and staff
Act as a resource for a school or unit
Abide by and follow the Harvard University IT technical standards, policies, and Code of Conduct
Basic Qualifications
Minimum of five years’ post-secondary education or relevant work experience
Additional Qualifications and Skills
Familiarity with;
modern data warehouses
Apex
Informatica ETL tool
Certificates and Licenses
Completion of Harvard IT Academy specified foundational courses (or external equivalent) preferred
Working Conditions
Work is performed in an office setting
Work Format Details
HUIT actively supports hybrid work where business needs allow. This position has been designated as a primarily remote position. While this position is primarily remote, travel to campus may be necessary based on business needs and the nature of work. Examples include bi-annual or quarterly Town Halls, critical business meetings or other work events. Additional details will be discussed during the interview process. All remote work must be performed within one of the Harvard Registered Payroll States, which currently includes Massachusetts, Connecticut, Maine, New Hampshire, Rhode Island, Vermont, Georgia, Illinois, Maryland, New Jersey, New York, Virginia, Washington, and California (CA for exempt positions only). Certain visa types and funding sources may limit work location. Individuals must meet work location sponsorship requirements prior to employment.
About Us
More about HUIT:
Harvard University Information Technology (HUIT) is a community of Information Technology professionals committed to delivering service and technological solutions in support of teaching, learning, research and administration. We are recruiting an IT workforce that has both breadth in their ability to collaborate and innovate across disciplines – and depth in specific areas of expertise. HUIT offers opportunities for IT professionals to learn and work in a unique technology landscape and service-focused environment.

Harvard University Information Technology (HUIT) is responsible for the strategy, planning, and delivery of information technology across the University. Our mission is to assure Harvard’s leadership in IT. We strive to make it easier for faculty, students, and staff to teach, research, learn and work through the effective use of information technology. HUIT’s core values are User Focused, Collaborative, Innovative and Open.

HUIT’s core values are:
User-focused
Collaborative
Innovative
Open
IT Academy (designed for IT Staff):
HUIT’s IT Academy aims to enable each IT staff person to grow professionally and become a trusted partner to her or his team. The IT Academy is built on the belief that every IT staff member across the University (including technology employees at each school and campus) can grow in her or his area of expertise as well as building strong people and project management skills. Learn more here: https://itacademy.harvard.edu/

description:
Department: Facilities Operations Management
Location: San Antonio, TX, US

NIKA is hiring for a Senior Data Analyst to provide support services to the Defense Health Agency (DHA) Portfolio Business Integration (PBI) Program based out of San Antonio, TX or Falls Church, VA!
Named a “Top Workplace” by the Washington Post, NIKA is a well-established company that is focused on growth within an entrepreneurial environment. We work with governments to operate and manage their real property. Our operations management, engineering, and project management services provide our customers with the value and expertise to ensure operational readiness for complex and mission-critical facilities.
Job Description and Tasks
Assists in the collection, analysis, and reporting of MHS data, with the intent of identifying opportunities for improvement in the use of DHA resources to improve health care delivery and contain costs involving multiple programs across the DHA. The work involves studying processes and operations, skillful data mining, routine analysis, and accurate modeling of information from multiple sources including but not limited to internet operating systems, M2, MDR, MIP, GENESIS, DMHRSi, DMLSS-FM, LogiCole, RPAD, and other data sources. Accurately builds and executes moderately complex queries in response to management questions, identifying and analyzing issues, applying statistical and/or operational analysis techniques, preparing reports of findings, and developing recommendations to resolve substantive problems impacting quality, effectiveness, efficiency, and costs in healthcare delivery.
Assists in building and maintaining models using facilities, environmental, clinical, operational, personnel, and cost/expense data in support of DHA FE.
Provides support to the government on the modification, implementation, integration, and sustainment of data and data processes, including data loading, processing, and standardization techniques using SQL queries and stored procedures.
Performs analytical studies using accepted data science techniques to provide insight into areas of trending/improvement opportunities based on FE data and leadership direction.
Prepares briefing charts, fact sheets, and staff reports complete with findings, analyses, recommendations, and other correspondence as needed.
Supports the business process documentation needs by creating and maintaining thorough documentation of database processes and procedures, including data mapping, data dictionaries and database diagrams.
Uses established and updated data science and analytical/statistical techniques/methodologies, tools, e.g., software.
Explores data, identify problems, and develop analytical plans accordingly.
Writes detailed specifications for analysis plans and data files. Apply descriptive and multivariate statistical methods.
Analyzes data and interpret results to identify significant differences in relationships.
Evaluates sources of information to determine any limitation in terms of reliability or usability.
Evaluates procedures used to obtain data to ensure validity, applicability, efficiency, and accuracy.
Identifies relationships and trends in data, as well as any factors that could affect results.
Validates, manipulates, and performs data analysis on large datasets and “big data”.
Interprets and presents results in a way that allows for effective decision making.
Develops system data models to aid descriptive and predictive analysis of the DHA facilities, and healthcare system.
Develops, maintains, and utilizes data management techniques such as relational databases to manage the flow of information between organizations and various information systems within the DHA, MHS or other Government agencies, where appropriate.
Builds predictive models using a variety of statistical, established, and innovative, techniques.
Assesses and continually monitors the performance of predictive models and the impact on related outcomes.
Develops automatic generation of standard updates covering modeling and performance metrics.
Tests and evaluate new software packages.
Provides consultation to clients or colleagues.
Required Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Health Services Research, Biostatistics, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or related quantitative field of study. Previous participation in advanced training/program in their area of expertise is required or equivalent combination of education and experience.
The Government may consider significant clinical/medical/facilities/health data experience such as previous participation in a(n) analytics/quantitative/informatics program as an appropriate substitute for education.
2 years of experience working in healthcare and facility data quality improvement.
2 years of experience developing and deploying clinical performance metrics.
3 years of experience with basic SQL for data manipulation and/or SAS statistical analysis software packages.
1 year of software management and data retrieval experience.
2+ years of statistical language experience such as R, Python, SPSS, or SAS
Must be a current citizen of the United States of America and eligible obtain a clearance.
Knowledge of relational database software; proficiency in applied statistics using SAS, SQL or other statistical programs.
Knowledge and mastery of a broad range of data analyses, mathematics, statistical analysis, modeling/simulation, and/or other scientific concepts, principles, standards, methods, techniques, practices, and procedures.
Knowledge in planning, coordinating, and executing complex studies applying modeling techniques and procedures.
Knowledge in analyzing data using probability statistics and trend analysis.
Knowledge of the concepts, principles, and practices related to data management, data reliability, data validity, and statistical analysis.
Knowledge in designing databases/spreadsheets to convey management level data in logical concise manner.
Knowledge of statistical and data warehousing software to support analytic efforts.
Knowledge of interactive data visualization products such as Tableau and QlikView.
Demonstrated communication skills to effectively organize and analyze information and produce authoritative reports, position papers, briefings and presentations that are clear, concise, engaging, convincing and effectively advocate/defend a position.
Demonstrated skill as an analytical and creative thinker, innovative problem solver, self-motivated and proactive and highly organized.
Skill in programming and the application of advanced techniques and data science to apply SQL hosted on enterprise and/or tactical computing infrastructures.
Skill in using open-source statistical packages (e.g., R, Python), and commercial analytic tools (e.g., Tableau, MS Excel).
Skill in applying intermediate to advanced data collection and analysis techniques in performing reviews and evaluation of programs from potentially disparate databases of demographic, financial, clinical, population health, and operational performance data.
Skill in using Microsoft office products; expert knowledge in designing databases/spreadsheets to convey management level data in a logical and concise manner; and use of automation and development of data extractions is required.
Awareness of information systems security principles and concepts to ensure all data analytics efforts are conducted in accordance with information security best practices.
Knowledge of missions, organizations, programs, and requirements of health care delivery Systems. This includes knowledge of the MHS facilities, resources, programs, serviced population, policies, and regulatory requirements.
Apply data visualization and integration services and techniques for presenting data and analytical results using various elements (graphs, charts, scorecards, dashboards, and presentations).
Proven ability to synthesize disparate data from multiple sources and coalesce into an accurate and useful analytic product, incorporating Service and MHS strategic goals for use by leadership in both tactical and strategic decision making.
Demonstrated ability to provide accurate and timely analytical products containing well-reasoned and cogent discussion points providing leadership with substantiated options or courses of action.
Demonstrated ability to organize/participate/lead working groups to develop analytic products and by products or to develop/understand processes leading to effective optimization of analytic efforts.
Demonstrated ability to communicate analytical discoveries and appropriate recommendations/mitigation strategies effectively and clearly to all levels of customers.
Demonstrated advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite/Microsoft 365 products PLUS additional software/hardware skills and capabilities.
Ability to critically examine, evaluate, and problem-solve.
Demonstrated ability to undertake and complete multiple tasks with multiple deadlines simultaneously.
Ability to deliver products on time, on schedule, within budget. Flexibility and ability to adapt to rapidly changing and often time-constrained environment.
Ability to acquire skills/capabilities necessary to meet growing needs/demands of systems/software/hardware.
Preferred Skills
Prior experience implementing or supporting clinical information systems experience; five (5) years’ experience in medical/clinical/health data, health care data analysis and management.
Advanced skill programming and the application of advanced operations research and data science to apply SQL hosted on enterprise and/or tactical computing infrastructures; advanced skills in using open-source statistical packages (e.g., R, Python), and commercial analytic tools (e.g., Tableau, MS Excel).
Demonstrated skill to handle-multiple and simultaneous tasks meeting aggressive deadlines.
Mastery in and skill in applying advanced statistical theories, principles, concepts, methods, techniques, practices and analysis to advise and propose the appropriate application of statistical techniques.
Comprehensive knowledge of design, programming, and analysis and statistical techniques utilizing advanced application of Statistical Analysis System (SAS).
Knowledge of the MHS direct care and purchased care health care delivery systems, aggregate health care data analysis, cost benefit analysis, and MHS business case tools.

Further, NIKA takes affirmative action to ensure that applicants are employed and employees are treated during employment without regard to any of these characteristics. Discrimination of any type will not be tolerated.

description:
Who we are and why you should join us:
As a consultant at Partner Forces, you will serve as a trusted advisor to our clients’ day in and day out. You will have the opportunity to collaborate with your colleagues, our partners, and our clients to ideate, initiate and complete tasks, projects, and initiatives. You will work on mission-oriented projects, where you will bring forward actionable insights, solve complex problems, and thrive on delivering meaningful solutions.
Partner Forces is grounded in our core values of integrity, diversity, positivity, candor, determination, and teamwork. Our culture is a reflection of this, ensuring that we:
Apply solution-oriented thinking to challenges and opportunities.
Thrive by remaining agile and embracing change.
Work to create an environment where everyone feels welcome and valued as teammates and contributors.
Bring out the best in others by applying sound judgment and exuding principled genuineness.
Embrace a continuous learning and growth mindset.
Encourage an open dialogue even when it is hard.
Continuously promoting teamwork and collaboration to achieve the best outcomes for our clients and teams.
As an employee at Partner Forces, you’ll join a diverse team of consultants who share a passion for prioritizing collaboration, crafting solutions to mitigate risk, protecting critical infrastructure and helping our national security and industry partner tackle their most pressing challenges. At Partner Forces, we take our employees’ well-being and growth as seriously as we do our mission. You will be challenged every day, but we know that business and individual growth go hand-in-hand, so we offer a wide array of benefits that support the well-being and personal and professional development of our employees.
What we are looking for:
Partner Forces is seeking a Data Analyst to support a Department of Homeland Security (DHS) client. This position will play a key role in supporting strategic initiatives for this agency. The primary responsibility set for this position involves collecting, consolidating and interpreting data, identifying trends, and communicating findings effectively to drive clients' mission-critical initiatives.
What you will do as a Data Analyst:
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets and apply advanced analytic and statistical techniques to derive insights.
Research, hypothesize and develop analytical approaches for identifying, analyzing, and interpreting trends or patterns in complex data sets.
Design and build analytics dashboards to measure performance and assist in directing team's efforts towards initiatives with the largest impact.
Develop compelling narratives and visualizations to communicate data findings to diverse stakeholders, including senior leadership.
Prepare and present detailed reports, dashboards, and presentations that translate complex data into understandable formats.
Create interactive dashboards and visual reports using Power BI to provide real-time data insights.
Establish and maintain effective working relationships with internal and external stakeholders.
Keep informed of the mission, organizational structure, key personnel, current activities, status of current projects, and any issues affecting the organization.
Qualifications:
US Citizen
Ability to obtain and maintain DHS HQ suitability required; current CISA preferred.
At least 8 years of experience.
BA/BS degree in relevant field of study (including but not limited to mathematics, economics, data science, statistics, etc.), and 5+ years of relevant professional experience required
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite applications, especially Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook.
Proficiency in using Power BI or Tableau for data visualization and developing dashboards.
Proficiency in using Python or R for data science: data wrangling, statistical analysis, machine learning models.
Strong communication/presentation skills and ability to explain technical topics to non-technical audiences.
Ability to design and deliver solutions independently and work collaboratively as part of a team.
Strong consulting skills: identifying and addressing client needs, building relationships, and driving initiatives forward.
At Partner Forces, we consider many factors when making compensation decisions, reflecting the unique skills and experiences each candidate brings, as well as organizational and contractual needs. An estimate of the salary range for this role is included here. We believe that salary is just one component of your total compensation package. Our goal is to support your growth and reward your contributions in a meaningful way. We look forward to exploring this further with you during the interview process.
Annual Salary Range
$80,000—$140,000 USD
The Company
Partner Forces, LLC., is a WOSB focused on helping homeland security partners with their most pressing and complex challenges and opportunities. The company provides management consulting services for the homeland security and national security enterprise. We offer clients holistic and integrated solutions to their current and emerging homeland security requirements related to program development and analysis, stakeholder engagement and outreach, strategic planning, technology implementation, security and preparedness assessment, and business process design and improvement.
Partner Forces values a diverse, inclusive workforce and we provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and employees. It is the policy of Partner Forces to comply with all federal and state laws concerning the employment of persons with disabilities and to act in accordance with regulations and guidance issued by the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) and state agencies. All qualified applicants for employment will be considered without regard to an individual’s race, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, religion, age, national origin or ancestry, citizenship, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, marital status, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, genetic information, military or veteran status, or any other basis protected by federal, state, or local laws. If you are unable to submit your application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at recruiting@partnerforces.com.

description:

The ideal candidate will have a strong background in data analysis, with the ability to interpret complex data sets and provide actionable insights. As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for collecting, processing, and analyzing data to support business decision-making and drive strategic initiatives.
Key Responsibilities:
Collect, process, and analyze large data sets to identify trends, patterns, and insights.
Develop and maintain dashboards and reports to track key performance indicators (KPIs) and business metrics.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand their data needs and provide analytical support.
Perform data validation and ensure data integrity and accuracy across all reports and analyses.
Conduct ad-hoc analyses to support various business initiatives and projects.
Utilize statistical methods and data visualization techniques to present findings in a clear and concise manner.
Identify opportunities for process improvements and recommend data-driven solutions.
Stay up-to-date with industry trends and best practices in data analysis and business intelligence.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or a related field; Master’s degree preferred.
3+ years of experience in data analysis or a related role.
Proficiency in SQL and experience with data analysis tools (e.g., Excel, R, Python).
Strong knowledge of data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Looker.
Experience with data warehousing concepts and ETL processes.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with a keen attention to detail.
Strong communication skills and the ability to present complex data findings to non-technical stakeholders.
Familiarity with statistical analysis and predictive modeling techniques is a plus.
Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment.
title: Data Analyst

description:
Abbott is a global healthcare leader that helps people live more fully at all stages of life. Our portfolio of life-changing technologies spans the spectrum of healthcare, with leading businesses and products in diagnostics, medical devices, nutritionals and branded generic medicines. Our 114,000 colleagues serve people in more than 160 countries.
Interested in applying your wealth of technical knowledge and experience towards an opportunity in the medical field and improving the lives of people with diabetes? The candidate will be responsible for collecting, cleaning, massaging and analysis of big data. The role will also contribute to defining and implementing Big Data Strategy for the organization along with driving the implementation of IT solutions for the business. The candidate will be working on a big data team to focus on applying data engineering, data science and machine learning approaches to solve business problems.

As a Data Analyst, you will play a crucial role in shaping our data-driven strategies and contributing to the success of our Big Data initiatives at ADC. You will be responsible for designing, developing and deploying advanced data science solutions to uncover customer, product and operational insights from complex datasets. Candidate should be able to work on a geographically distributed team. Additionally, they will be working in a technology-driven environment utilizing the latest tools and techniques.
The ideal candidate should have rigorous analytical capabilities and a pragmatic mindset to help solve our most complex business problems. Highly sought-after qualities include versatility and a desire to continuously learn, improve and empower the team.
Responsibilities
Data Analysis and Modeling:
Craft and maintain data infrastructure with the Data Engineering team by translating business requirements from business partners to data models that will enable reporting, dashboards and segmentation
Proactively analyze data and trends to provide insights and recommendations that drive business strategies
Data Visualization:
Create and maintain dashboards and reports using data visualization tools to communicate findings and insights to technical and non-technical stakeholders
Data Optimization:
Continuously monitor and improve data quality, accuracy and efficiency of data processes, including data cleaning and transformation
Define and maintain a central source of truth and normalizing data
Data Security:
Contribute to data security and confidentiality by maintaining appropriate access controls, encryption and backup procedures
Team Collaboration:
Collaborate with cross-functional teams including R&D, Global Strategic Marketing, Quality, etc. to identify data needs and provide data-driven solutions
Training and Delivery:
Provide training and support to team and business partners to enhance data literacy
Respond to ad-hoc data requests and perform special analyses as required by the business to support strategic decision-making
Innovate:
Stay updated with the latest developments in data science and machine learning to continually improve data analysis methodologies and techniques
Identify opportunities for innovation and propose data-driven solutions
Documentation:
Maintain comprehensive documentation of data analysis processes, methodologies and findings
Required Qualifications
Bachelor’s Degree in a relevant field (e.g., Statistics, Data Science, Economics, Computer Science) plus at least 4-6 years of recent experience
Experience with data exploration, data cleaning, data analysis, data visualization and data mining, preferably in the medical device or healthcare industry
Experience with SQL, building dashboards, data transformation and analysis tools (ie Python, R)
Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Databricks, QuickSight, Power BI)
Strong knowledge of data governance principles, data integration, data warehousing and ETL processes
Familiarity with data privacy and security regulations, such as HIPAA and GDPR
Ability to work collaboratively in a fast-paced, cross-functional team environment
Excellent communication and presentation skills with the ability to translate technical findings into actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders
Comfortable working asynchronously with a distributed team
Preferred Qualifications
Education in, or experience with, machine learning
Experience working in an agile environment

The base pay for this position is $83,600.00 – $167,200.00. In specific locations, the pay range may vary from the range posted.

description:

TASI JUNIOR DATA ANALYST – ID# 224647.

Regular, Full-Time, RCUH Non-Civil Service position with the Social Science Research Institute (SSRI), Telecommunication and Social Informatics (TASI) Research Program, located at the University of Hawai‘i in Honolulu, Hawai‘i. Telework (from employee’s residence and ) may be permissible subject to review and approval by Principal Investigator and RCUH. Continuation of employment is dependent upon program/operational needs, satisfactory work performance, availability of funds, and compliance with applicable Federal/State laws.
MONTHLY SALARY RANGE: $5,000 - $8,000/Mon.
DUTIES: Facilitates data analysis, modeling, forecasting, statistical analysis, machine learning, as appropriate; including conceptualizing and designing health care cost studies based on demographics and patient condition (e.g. morbidity and comorbidities). Calculates and prepares information on the relevance, accuracy, and limitations of results. Utilizes reproducible reporting workflows. Builds and automates data products for effective communication, including but not limited to visualizations, reports, and dashboards. Prepares graphical presentations of data and infographics to communicate results to policymakers, program managers, health care professionals, and the public. Assists with developing recommendations based on findings. Documents analytic decisions, processes, assumptions, caveats, and methods. Integrates new data sources, which include data mapping, and extract, transform, and load (ETL) process development, data product development, and data management processes. Works with team to develop, implement, and document codes to perform quality checks, business rules, and data enhancements (e.g., claims versioning, groupers, classification algorithms, etc.) in new or existing data sources. Assists with improving data and platforms for the benefit of all users. Develops subject matter expertise in data sets. Assists with research questions and analytics requests.
PRIMARY QUALIFICATIONS:
EDUCATION
Bachelor’s Degree from an accredited four (4) year college or university in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics, Math, Statistics, Social Science, Management Information Systems, Information Technology, Public Health, or related field.
EXPERIENCE
Three to five (3-5) years of relevant work experience with data analysis, data modeling, business intelligence, reporting, and programming; working in an implemented software development life cycle environment; data analysis and visualization concepts; data analytic and visualization tools relevant to the project; working with or within healthcare data management. (Master’s Degree from an accredited college or university in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics, Math, Statistics, Social Science, Management Information Systems, Information Technology, Public Health, or related field may substitute for two (2) years of relevant work experience.)
KNOWLEDGE
Good working knowledge of research methodologies, study designs, and analytical techniques (including but not limited to data dredging, predictive analytics, precision and bias, survival analysis, machine learning). Good working knowledge of healthcare claims data, healthcare coding structures such as ICD-9/ICD-10 diagnosis codes, CPT/HCPCS procedure codes, HL7, NDC codes, therapeutic classifications, healthcare clinical data or public health data. Basic knowledge of U.S. health systems and payer-provider relationship, including major system stakeholders, providers and provider types, provider services, healthcare billing and coding, and claims processing. Basic knowledge of Medicaid, Medicare, Children’s Health Insurance Programs, including statutory authorities, regulations, and other guidance. Basic knowledge of data resources of the federal government, including data acquisition processes and requirements. Basic knowledge of 835, 837 i/p/d EDI ANSI X.12 and pharmacy claims data structures and data fields including, NCPDP D.0. Working knowledge of research, studies, and literature on morbidities, comorbidities, and relationship to health care costs.
ABILITIES & SKILLS
Ability to conceptualize research questions and appropriate methodologies for data analysis. Problem-solving skills. Excellent communication skills. Ability to effectively conduct work remotely (e.g., telework) as applicable. Must be able to pass a post offer criminal background check. Must be able to complete the UH Information Security Awareness Training (ISAT) within two (2) weeks from date of hire, and re-certify every twelve (12) months.
PHYSICAL/MEDICAL DEMANDS
Able to lift and carry up to fifty (50) pounds unassisted to support moving equipment or supplies for the project (e.g., tables, chairs, computers, data and network equipment).
POLICY/REGULATORY REQUIREMENT
As a condition of employment, employee will be subject to all applicable RCUH policies, procedures, and trainings and, as applicable, subject to the University of Hawai‘i's TASI/PHIDC Research Program HIPAA/PHI privacy and security policy and the HIPAA/PHI privacy and security policy of various cooperating entities/organizations. Violation of the RCUH's, the UH's, or the business entity's policies and/or procedures or applicable State or Federal laws and/or regulations may lead to disciplinary action (including, but not limited to possible termination of employment, personal fines, civil and/or criminal penalties, etc.). Must complete the University of Hawai‘i's TASI/PHIDC Center Research Program HIPAA/PHI privacy and security training and the HIPAA/PHI privacy and security of various cooperating entities/organizations, training immediately after hire or not later than employee’s initial exposure to HIPAA/PHI. Must maintain a current status on the University’s and/or the business entity's training requirements.
SECONDARY QUALIFICATIONS:
High proficiency in analyzing large and complex healthcare data sets. Experience with health insurance and billing workflows, actuarial analysis. Experience working in a healthcare setting. Experience with database management and performance tuning. Experience with front-end web design. Experience working with healthcare claims, public health, or clinical data. Experience with operational protocols relating to HIPAA and Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health (HITECH) laws and regulations preferred. Certification in health analytics.
APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS: Please go to https://www.rcuh.com/work/careers/. You must submit the following documents online to be considered for the position: 1) Cover Letter, 2) Resume, 3) Professional References, 4) Copy of Degree(s)/Transcript(s)/Certificate(s). All online applications must be submitted/received by the closing date (11:59 P.M. Hawai‘i Standard Time/RCUH receipt time) as stated on the job posting.If you do not have access to our system and the closing date is imminent, you may send additional documents to rcuh_recruitment @rcuh.com. If you have questions on the application process and/or need assistance, please call (808)956-7262 or (808)956-0872. Please visit https://www.rcuh.com/document-library/3-000/benefits/rcuh-benefits-at-a-glance/ for more information on RCUH’s Benefits for eligible employees.
RCUH’s mission is to support and enhance research, development and training in Hawai‘i, with a focus on the University of Hawai‘i.

description:
Position Summary:

The Business Data Analyst will be responsible for driving key strategic inititaves to improve the brands position within the current and target markets. Key functions will include the collection, analysis and reporting of sales/orders/market related data. This position will assit the VP/GM in guiding pricing recommendations, planning, and forecasting through the creation of custom reports.

Principle Duties (includes, but is not limited to):

Strategy development and deployment
o Lead data analysis and generation of insights related to 80-20 including various elements such as quad analysis, identifying work drivers, product line simplification options, customer line simplification options
o Lead research and analysis for business teams as a part of Grassroots strategy development to assess market sizing, competitive landscape, value chain analysis, economic value assessment, voice of customer, customer segmentation, commercialization plans and industrialization plans for strategic growth initiatives.
o Support the research and analysis required to support the annual 3 year Strategic plan and 1 year Operational plan
o Assists VP/GM with project management / Stage gate tracking for NPD projects.

Business Analytics
o Support co-ordination across various product lines to track and consolidate key commercial metrics such as share gain, price, mix, market data etc.
o Support development of market input for Resistoflex by analyzing external market trends, earnings calls, tracking competitors and key customers
o Track and manage sales analytics, industry/performance trends, and industry event insights
o Reporting and analysis including executive reporting of sales and marketing results, key metrics and KPIs, campaign tracking and analysis, and ad hoc strategic analysis.
o Prepares monthly and weekly reports to be used by group management by consolidating data from varios sources.
o Prepares templates to be used throughout group for various tasks (eg month-end, forecasts, etc). Recommends revisions to existing reports, or assists in the development of new reporting tools as needed.
o Assists VP/GM with SIOP process, annual operating plan preparation, monthly pulse, quarterly forecasts, and weekly pulses (mini-forecast of month and quarter).
o Supports research and analysis for Brand product sourcing strategy and supports creation and development of business models.
o Develops product application training material.
o Monitors competitor marketing and pricing activities, and develops counter strategies.
o Participates actively in the Quality and CBS processes including project team involvement, problem solving, and recommending solutions to improve and enhance the quality of departmental and/or company-wide activities.
o Handles confidential and sensitive information.
o Performs other duties and projects as assigned.

Essential Qualifications / Experience:

Undergraduate degree in Chemical, Materials or Mechanical Engineering
MBA with preferred concentrations of Strategy, Finance or Marketing
At least 2 years of work experience in chemical or pharmaceutical or energy industry.
Business analytics experience
Ability to be review and analyze prospective company and sales data
Exceptional interpersonal, communication, and presentation skills with ability to quickly build relationships with those inside and outside the business.
Excellent written and oral communications skills
Excellent project management skills
Effective time management skills
Maintain the highest level of confidentiality, professionalism, diplomacy and moral ethic when communicating with employees and customers.
Ability to prioritize tasks while being flexible to the dynamic needs and changes of management, customers and VP/GM.
Multilingual language skills are a plus

description:

The Operations Data Analyst plays a key role in supporting data integrity, data governance, and the utilization of data to grow and optimize the business via data entry, reporting, modeling, and analytics. This position will work with Operations Data Analyst and internal stakeholders to create, update, and maintain customer records as well as develop an understanding of organizational needs and business drivers leading to reporting and analytics products that communicate key findings to stakeholders and facilitate data-driven decision making. The analyst will input data as well as leverages large and varied datasets to support initiatives while promoting standardizations and best practices to enable effective use of data throughout the enterprise.
Location: Indianapolis, Indiana; we are seeking candidates that currently reside in the central Indiana region; within approximately a 70 mile range of Indianapolis. Our Central (Corporate) Office is located on the northwest side of Indianapolis. Position is hybrid (a mix of remote & in-office, as well as any necessary business travel).
Relocation is not available for this position
Immigration sponsorship not available for this position
Applicants can expect a compensation of $60,000 per year for this opportunity.
Responsibilities
Data Entry and Data Management
Collaborate with internal stakeholders to input data to create, update, and maintain customer records.
Review data for deficiencies and errors.
Assist with special projects that require large amounts of data entry.
Support various departments with data entry support on an ad-hoc basis.
Work to continuously improve data entry and data analytics business processes
Data Analytics and Reporting
Collaborate with cross-functional business leaders to understand and document reporting and analytics needs.
Support stakeholders via reporting, modelling, and analytics.
Develop and implement analytic models, predictive tools, and applications to meet business needs.
Conduct targeted analysis on categories, business units, equipment type, equipment make/model, and or suppliers.
Work with field leadership and functional area leaders to establish and visualize key operational measures.
Identify key metrics and build executive dashboards to track progress of the business and its highest priority initiatives.
Tools and Processes
Support the Operations Data Analytics team in presenting complex data in visually compelling, digestible, and informative ways.
Based on data analysis results and organizational feedback, partner with cross-functional areas in the development of new processes, products, services, or relationships.
Support the integration of team processes and work products into automated systems and tools.
Develop best practices and business rules to ensure uniformity in work, deliverables, and outcomes.
Plan new programs in response to new business needs, assess the value of new technologies, and guide the creation of innovative solutions.
Analyze operational business performance; design and execute research, models and other mechanisms to identify, evaluate and prioritize opportunities.
Coordinates with peers in cross-functional areas on a jointly defined and managed dataset supporting organization-wide analytical initiatives.
Communication and Interactions
Create and deliver presentations and communications to peers, functional area leaders, and executives.
Collaborate with financial planning and analysis to ensure accuracy and clarity in analytics and reports.
Work collectively with finance to ensure operational processes and initiatives are tracked to the bottom line.
Seek input from cross-functional experts as needed to gather data for the analysis process.
Develop presentations to be shared with executive leadership on monthly metrics and strategic initiatives.
All other duties as assigned.
Skills and Experience
Highly proficient with Microsoft Office applications; Excel knowledge is required
Foundational SQL skills preferred (Snowflake experience preferred)
Familiarity with a scripting languages or statistical software (Python/R/Matlab/C++/Java) preferred
Familiarity with reporting tools (e.g., Qlik, Tableau, Power BI) preferred
Interest and familiarity in designing and developing compelling and interactive data visualizations
Experience with complex data analysis, statistical modeling, and quantitative/qualitative models preferred.
Demonstrated experience with predictive analytics strongly preferred
Knowledge of healthcare industry, clinical engineering, medical technology, and/or healthcare support services preferred
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with an acute attention to detail
Creative thinker with the ability to prioritize work and manage time amidst multiple tasks
Ability to effectively communicate and collaborate in cross-functional teams
Strong written and verbal communication skills supporting interactions with personnel at all levels within the organization
Education and Qualifications
Associates degree in Data Analytics, Computational Statistics, Applied Statistics (math, statistics, engineering, computer science, business) or equivalent experience is required

Project management experience.
Strong human relations and communication skills; communicate clearly and professionally both verbally and in writing; respond openly to requests and concerns.

Novelis is one of the world leaders in aluminum recycling and rolling and a leading sustainable aluminum solutions provider. Driven by our purpose of “shaping a sustainable world together” we work alongside our customers to provide innovative solutions to the aerospace automotive beverage packaging and specialty markets. Headquartered in Atlanta Georgia Novelis has approximately 13000 employees in 32 operating facilities on 4 continents.

Position Overview
The Global HR Process Excellence team, located in Atlanta, GA, is seeking a Senior Data Analyst, People Analytics! The purpose of this position is to provide decision making support to HR by providing advanced data analyses and consulting to HR: Provide data-driven insights to support strategic HR decisions, such as workforce planning, talent acquisition, and employee development and to drive business value by leveraging the unknown value of people behavior data for the business.

Collaborate with stakeholders to gather requirements and drive adoption of solutions.
Identify business trends and problems through complex data analysis.
Apply and integrate statistical, mathematical, and predictive modeling to manipulate complex data from a variety of sources to impact business partner decision making.
Develop, analyze, and model workforce, operational, economic, management, financial and other organizational data to quantify performance of business segments and evaluate potential operational changes.
Use and analyze existing data science solutions to perform tasks in a reproducible, repeatable manner.
Be able to automate the collection and analysis of large datasets, to improve every phase of the HR pipeline, from recruitment and compensation to promotion, training, and evaluation and creating business value.
Collaborate with members of People Analytics, HRIS teams to deliver complete analytics solutions to business partners.

Instead, we focus on developing products and services that allow us to better serve our customers and the communities around us and help our members achieve their best possible health and quality of life.

In this position...
Data Analytics position within Powertrain Engineering, working on quality data analysis, insights, and presentation material for executive level management reviews.



Ford ICE, Propulsion and Thermal Systems Engineering (IPTSE) Quality Team is looking for a Data Analytics Specialist to support our team by analyzing and interpreting warranty and connected vehicle data indicators to focus the team on emerging issues and key insights. This role will involve developing data solutions for internal customers and working with the engineering teams on the use of data for problem solving. We are looking for someone who has a passion for growing their skills, tackling exciting “leading edge” work, has a passion for customer quality, and likes problem solving potential concerns.



What you'll do...
Day to day responsibilities will include analyzing data from Ford’s internal warranty system, as well as multiple big data sources that will be used in creating executive level presentations. These presentations will include charts and narrative writing that clearly tell the story that the data is telling us, as well as insights that our team would like to highlight to upper management. Another part of this role will be working with the greater Powertrain team in data requests as needed.

Warranty Data Analysis

Presentation information gathering

Analyzing collected data and putting it into a format that others can easily interpret

Assist with executive level presentation preparation

Execute various quality data requests from the IPTSE organization

Work with PD teams to extract, summarize, and analyze Warranty and Connected Vehicle data to further understand and problem solve potential issues

Work with the IPTSE team to enhance the use of Connected Vehicle data (e.g., engine speed, vehicle speed, warning lights, etc.) through the ideation and development of tools/methods for problem solving

Work with the IPTSE team to develop processes, tools and methods to obtain insight from large files of Connected Vehicle data

Promote and use Agile Data Collection methods (RDR, PARSED, CARMon, ADC Lua Scripting) in support of engineering problem solving and data-driven decisions

Build strong and trusting relationships with business partners across Ford North American organizations




You'll have...
Bachelor of Science degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Computer Science or related field

1+ years of experience in Big Data Analytics

1+ years of experience in query languages, SQL, Google BigQuery, or Spark

1+ years of experience with visualization skills in communicating data insights to make data analysis measurable and understandable by business partners




Even better, you may have...
Master’s Degree or above in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Computer Science or related field

3+ years of experience in Big Data Analytics

2+ years of experience in query languages: SQL, Google BigQuery, or Spark.

Proven skills in team building, implementing process improvements, problem solving, and consistent delivery to objectives

Ability to take complex problems and break them down to build and implement an action plan

Strong collaboration and communication skills, ability to engage with upper management and peers

Self-motivated individual with a high level of initiative

Ability to prioritize in a fast-paced, sophisticated, global environment

Strong organizational and time management skills with the ability to coordinate multiple teams and projects

Ability to consistently perform at a high level of technical competence, showing composure and decisiveness under pressure

Excellent interpersonal, written, and oral communication skills

Ability to understand how to ingest large data sets from a variety of sources (SQL, Python, Java, Alteryx, Qlik Sense, etc.)

Expertise to manipulate data to form unified data sets for analysis.

Knowledge of data management

Experience with Automotive systems, features, and/or components

You may not check every box, or your experience may look a little different from what we've outlined, but if you think you can bring value to Ford Motor Company, we encourage you to apply!
As an established global company, we offer the benefit of choice. You can choose what your Ford future will look like: will your story span the globe, or keep you close to home? Will your career be a deep dive into what you love, or a series of new teams and new skills? Will you be a leader, a changemaker, a technical expert, a culture builder…or all of the above? description:
