Aurora considers candidates without regard to their race, color, religion, national origin, age, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, marital status, pregnancy status, parent or caregiver status, ancestry, political affiliation, veteran and/or military status, physical or mental disability, or any other status protected by federal or state law. Aurora considers qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. We are also committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at careersiteaccommodations@aurora.tech.
For California applicants, information collected and processed as part of your application and any job applications you choose to submit is subject to Aurora's California Employment Privacy Policy.
Diversity, Equity and Inclusion
At Aurora, every employee is empowered to take an active role in building an inclusive, collaborative, and unified culture that leverages our diverse strengths, perspectives, and backgrounds.
Transforming how the world moves people and goods involves seeking to understand backgrounds, insights, and lived experiences that differ from our own. One way we accomplish that is with our 15 employee-led Aurora Unified Groups, which support diverse voices and drive inclusive collaboration. We believe that teamwork, belonging, and trust motivate and support our employees to do their best work. As our team grows, we strive to attract and retain exceptional talent that adds new perspectives and experiences and continues to drive innovation. Learn more on our Culture Page.
We are committed to helping qualified military community members leverage their talents in service of our mission. To understand how your military experience aligns with career opportunities at Aurora, review your military job classification at MyNextMove.org and consider applying for open positions corresponding to your identified skills and experiences!

To enhance the overall value of the company with the implementation and adoption of Data Driven Decision Support through:
Leadership of an enterprise strategic data governance process
Leadership of an enterprise strategic data management team
Governance of the production of high quality, immutable data (Golden Records) on which critical decision support platforms can rely – Strategic Data
Governance of the strategic intelligence logic and platforms that produce all decision support information for the business

Facilitating organizational alignment with a data and information driven decision-making culture

Preferred:

The Opportunity:
You will provide critical support to U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE), Homeland Security Investigations (HSI). You will use your skills to provide data collection, analysis, management, interpretation, visualization, and reporting; advanced statistical analysis, predictive modeling, forecasting, and inferences; tool development and model building to enhance data-driven, fact-based decision making; management and business process modeling; budget and workforce planning, formulation, justification, and forecasting; strategic planning and implementation; risk assessment and management; performance measure development and reporting; program development; research and program evaluation planning and implementation. You will provide supervision, management, industry knowledge, training, documentation, and technical/analytical support

Responsibilities:
You will support ICE by:
Presenting analyses in a cohesive manner using summary statistics (frequencies, averages, summations, filtering, etc.)
Applying standard statistical methods, appropriate to the data, such as correlations, weighting, ratios, trend analysis, hypothesis testing, regression, time series, optimization, cost analysis, systems modeling, risk modeling, simulation, predictive modeling and forecasting, and decision trees
Conducting reviews to find the best methods/techniques to address analytical questions
Documenting research questions, approach, progress, assumptions, and caveats throughout the data analysis process
Interpreting data, drawing sound, relevant, and defensible conclusions from the data analysis or models to effectively communicate findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. Conclusions must include recommended actions and must be framed within the context and scope of the question
Gathering information from various sources and assemble the information into comprehensive work products (reports, briefings, white papers, executive summaries, etc.)
Creating and presenting analyses in writing or orally via presentation for varying level of audiences from analytical expert to non-technical leader on the intent, purpose, scope, analysis, and results of all assigned projects and efforts.

Qualifications:
-DHS/ICE, DOD, or other federal agency clearance
-At least five (5) years of relevant experience
-Master’s degree (MA/MS) in Business Administration, Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a similar field. Equivalent experience in lieu of a MA/MS: Bachelor’s degree (BA/BS) in Business Administration, Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a similar field, plus an additional two (2) years’ of relevant experience in each of the area below
-Five (5) years of experience each of the following:
Coordinating the development of, and aligning a strategic plan with multiple external partners, and researching plan authorities.
Developing strategic implementation plans, communication plans, and performance measures that enable the agency to demonstrate progress towards attaining the goals of the plan
Managing projects to include gathering information from various sources and assembling the information into a comprehensive work product for leadership decisions, in addition to working with a variety of diverse and complicated projects and performing under tight time constraints
Using confidential or sensitive data; completing strategic planning activities with aggressive timeframes; working with multiple partners, including partners that may not be familiar with strategic planning; and leading senior-level working groups
-Three (3) years of experience designing and implementing an evaluation research project to include identifying the problem statement or research questions; designing logic models and outcomes; drafting flowcharts; implementing the program; gathering and analyzing data and metrics; assessing outcomes; and drawing conclusions to make recommendations about the viability and effectiveness of the program. Familiarity with the Foundations for Evidence-Based Policymaking Act of 2018 preferred.

Senior Data Analyst
We will count on you to:
Build automated systems that benchmark key aspects of insurance company performance against peers and support advisory solutions. Develop, implement, and maintain leading-edge data analytics systems that enable efficient gathering, reporting and presenting data for advisory solutions. Be a trusted leader and resource for maintaining and improving data in various cloud and on-premises data warehouses storing critical databases. Design processes to improve efficiency and volume of data that can be analyzed to develop insights into clients' strategic opportunities and risks. Under the supervision of North America Head of BI, design, structure, analyze, and scrub databases of the insurance market and macro-economic information leveraging various external and internal datasets. Develop expert knowledge of GC proprietary systems (Cognos, BenchmaRQ, Metarisk, and claims dashboard), create standard and ad hoc enquiries, search out commercial value add in the data (patterns, trends and correlations etc.) and respond on a timely basis to broker queries. Curate information through text mining queries and corresponding data visualization to communicate risk insights to clients/stakeholders. Interpret and analyze company financial data to identify trends and opportunities in observed data. Provide data support for Request for Proposals (RFP). Assist in the development of presentations and respond to ad-hoc data enquiries. Support data needs for capital models to support clients' financial strength ratings. Establish and maintain strong relationships with internal and external clients.
What you need to have:
Must have a Master’s degree or foreign equivalent in Computer Science, Data Science, Information Systems, Computer Engineering, or a related field plus one (1) year of experience in the position offered, as a Software Engineer, Data Analyst, or a related position. Employer will accept pre- or post- Master’s degree experience. In the alternative, employer will accept a Bachelor’s degree or foreign equivalent in Computer Science, Data Science, Information Systems, Computer Engineering, or a related field plus three (3) years of experience in the position offered, as a Software Engineer, Data Analyst, or a related position. Must have one (1) year (or three [3] years with a Bachelor’s) of experience with all of the following: Programming in Python, R, Java or .Net for data extraction, manipulation, and analysis; Implementing scalable web dynpro and EJB applications using the SAP Netweaver Portal to help analyze insurance data, monitor performance and build a reliable information management system; Designing high-quality database solutions in PostgreSQL and MS SQL by writing SQL queries, stored procedures, views, functions, joins, and subqueries; Designing and implementing data pipelines, continuously expanding them through extraction, transformation, and loading activities using SQL and Microsoft Excel; Creating Excel templates with advanced functions (including Pivot table, VLOOKUP, Charts, Analysis, Power view, Formulas, VBA & Macros) for large datasets, enabling the identification of key trends and patterns; Developing reports, visualizations, and presentations using Microsoft PowerPoint to communicate strategic findings and presenting recommendations to key stakeholders for informed business decisions; Generating data models and visualization dashboards using knowledge of business principles, insurance accounting standards and insurance capital model frameworks. Travel requirement: 10% domestic and international travel is required to various and unanticipated company and client sites.

description:
Summary:
Job Title: Data Analyst II
FLSA Status: Exempt
Location: Remote
Salary: $105,000 - $125,000

SUMMARY

The Data Analyst II is responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting data related to grant management and project performance. This role involves developing and maintaining dashboards to monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) and providing data-driven insights to support decision-making processes. The Data Analyst II plays a critical role in ensuring data integrity, supporting data management systems, and enhancing the overall data analysis capabilities within the organization. In the absence of a Financial Analyst, the Data Analyst may assume additional responsibilities related to financial data analysis.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

Data Collection and Analysis: Gather, process, and analyze data related to grant management and project performance. Use advanced analytical techniques to interpret complex data sets and provide insights that inform decision-making and strategic planning.
Dashboard Development and Maintenance: Design, develop, and maintain dashboards that track key performance indicators (KPIs) related to grants and project performance. Ensure dashboards are user-friendly, accurate, and provide real-time insights for stakeholders.
Data Management and Quality Assurance: Manage master data, including creation, updates, and deletion. Implement quality assurance protocols to ensure the accuracy and reliability of imported data. Work closely with quality assurance analysts to maintain data integrity.
Reporting and Documentation: Generate detailed analytical reports that summarize data findings, trends, and recommendations. Support the development of training materials and user guides for end-users. Ensure all reports and documentation comply with organizational standards and federal guidelines.
Collaboration and Technical Support: Collaborate with project managers, grant managers, and other stakeholders to support data-driven initiatives. Provide technical expertise on data storage structures, data mining, and data cleansing. Assist with troubleshooting issues related to the reporting database environment.
System Management and Optimization: Manage and design the reporting environment, including data sources, security, and metadata. Support the data warehouse by identifying and revising reporting requirements. Evaluate and implement new software solutions to enhance data analysis capabilities.
Training and User Support: Train end-users on new reports, dashboards, and data management tools. Provide ongoing support and technical assistance to ensure users can effectively utilize data insights for decision-making.
Confidential Data Handling: Ensure all data processing activities comply with federal privacy and confidentiality guidelines. Handle sensitive information with the highest level of security and discretion.
Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS

Proficient in data analysis, data management, and reporting tools.
Experience in developing and maintaining dashboards for tracking KPIs.
Strong knowledge of data integrity, data cleansing, and metadata standards.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets.
Strong technical skills in data storage, database management, and data mining.
Effective communication skills, capable of translating complex technical information into understandable terms for non-technical stakeholders.
Proficiency in using software solutions for large-scale database management.
EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE

Bachelor’s degree with 8-10 years of experience, or a Master’s degree with 6-8 years of experience in data analysis, data management, computer science, or a related field.
Experience working with large data sets and relational databases is required.
Familiarity with grant management and project performance metrics is preferred.
SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITY

No direct supervisory responsibilities. However, the Data Analyst II may provide technical guidance and support to junior analysts or team members involved in data-related tasks.
WORK ENVIRONMENT

The work environment is primarily office-based, involving collaboration with team members and interaction with stakeholders, with occasional offsite meetings and travel as required.
Our Values:
Native American Owned & Proud | Accountable | Team Focused | Innovative | Visionary | Excellence

PHYSICAL DEMANDS

These positions are mainly sedentary, involving extended periods of sitting, computer use, and occasional light lifting of office materials up to 20 pounds.
AAP/EEO Statement

Ho-Chunk, Inc. is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran. However, preference may be extended to persons of Indian descent in accordance with applicable laws.

Job Description:

Position Overview
Medical Data Analyst shall provide health care support at Fort Belvoir Community Hospital (FBCH), Fort Belvoir, VA. The contractor will work in conjunction with other health care providers, professionals, and noncontract personnel.
This opportunity is for a POTENTIAL CONTRACT award and is contingent upon the contract being awarded. Consideration for a potential contract may require a signed letter of intent. If the contract is awarded, another position posting will be available on the Company Careers portal.
Specific Duties/Tasks the Contractor Shall Perform:
1. Coordinates and provides consultation on multiple projects, studies, and systems analyses associated with health care programs and systems.
2. Conducts both quantitative and qualitative analyses in support of clinical and business workflow processes and recommends the planning for corrective courses of actions.
3. Communicates with clinics to diagnose business problems, develops, and presents appropriate sets of tools and applications as a solution and provides training to clients.
4. Supports the Chief and Deputy of Clinical Systems Support Department in terms of technical and administrative task requirements on a daily basis with strict adherence to suspense dates, information accuracy, and professional quality of work.

8. Implements VBA programming with clear and organized code documentation as well as comments to automate processes that support departmental mission of work and increase business efficiency.
9. Presents information derived from data and process analyses to various clients with proficiency in oral, visual, and written communications.
10. Completes all assigned actions and tasks within suspense period.
11. Reports to the department Chief, Deputy, and appropriate team leads of work progress, task status, and key findings on a daily basis.
12. Communicates with internal and external customers and visitors to the office.
13. Maintains and submits records of payroll timecards and Defense Medical Human Resources System-internet (DMHRSi) in a timely and accurate manner.

title: Data Analyst

description:
Description
ICF is seeking a Data Analyst to provide qualitative and quantitative analytic support for the implementation, execution, and evaluation of a technology-centric approach for treating mental health conditions across our active-duty military members and veterans. This approach will be executed as a pilot study at a controlled number of locations to evaluate the efficacy (among other performance measures) of training non-licensed mental health professionals on the use of behavioral health-related mobile apps. This critical work is aimed at reducing suicide across our active-duty military and veteran populations.
As a member of a multi-disciplinary team comprised of Psychologists and training experts, this position will play a key role in collecting, analyzing, and synthesizing data (qualitative and quantitative) collected from various stakeholders and behavioral health providers. The outcomes of the pilot study will be used to inform the effective implementation of selected apps into behavioral health care, advance accessibility and efficacy of care, apply and advance implementation science, and provide education to engage use of mobile apps throughout the care continuum and in the non-clinical community.
Key Responsibilities:
Provide data analysis subject matter expertise to develop, or assist in the development of, detailed analysis plans that map to the intended program outcomes and metrics.
Map analysis plans to appropriate analytic approaches and strategies to ensure accurate and meaningful data interpretation.
Use appropriate analytic approaches/strategies to execute/assist with data analysis, and deliver de-identified analytic datasets, data dictionaries, coding syntax.
Monitor pilot progress and evaluate outcomes related to the SocioTech integration of mobile behavioral health into clinical care.
Employ appropriate validated measures and develop evidence-informed surveys to collect quantitative and qualitative data from patients, behavioral health providers, and site leaders.
Complete necessary requirements pertinent to the collection of data using novel survey instrumentation developed by the contract.
Conduct Final Data Analyses.
Capture metrics of the success of this effort to inform the Military Health System (MHS) enterprise.
Ensure that all data collection and analysis activities comply with relevant ethical and regulatory standards.
Translate knowledge gained via the pilot study by contributing to the development of a final report and out briefings for leadership and stakeholders.
Develop or refine a variety of written documentation to disseminate findings of the pilot study.
Mandatory Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Public Health, or a related field (Master’s degree preferred).
5+ years of experience in data analysis, preferably in a public health, healthcare, or behavioral health setting.
5+ years of experience utilizing excellent communication and analytical skills, with the ability to translate complex data into actionable insights
5+ years of experience operating as a member of a team supporting multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment with diverse stakeholders.
5+ years of experience articulating and understanding of regulatory compliance and licensure requirements related to data collection and analysis.
5+ years of prior experience developing and executing detailed analysis plans.
3+ years of experience utilizing advanced data management and analysis features in MS Excel.
2+ years of experience using SAS (or comparable statistical analysis software) to support data analysis.
Beneficial Qualifications:
Master’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Public Health, or a related field.
Prior experience as a federal contractor.
Experience working with healthcare or public health data, particularly in mental health or mobile health integration.
Ability and experience communicating effectively (speaking and writing) to diverse audiences in order to convey clinical processes, problems, and solutions.

description:
Req ID: 32869
Summary
Data Analyst
Alexandria, VA
Are you ready to enhance your skills and build your career in a rapidly evolving business climate? Are you looking for a career where professional development is embedded in your employer’s core culture? If so, Chenega Military, Intelligence & Operations Support (MIOS) could be the place for you! Join our team of professionals who support large-scale government operations by leveraging cutting-edge technology and take your career to the next level!
As one of the newest Chenega companies, Chenega Defense & Aerospace Solutions (CDAS) was developed with the purpose of providing expert Engineering and Technical Support Services to federal customers.
The Data Analyst will analyze a large variety of documents to ensure proper placement in physical files, perform high-level scanning of master file documents to convert them into an electronic format and provide meticulous organization and management of case files, including sorting and categorizing documents before scanning.
Responsibilities
Work within the Standard Operating Procedure for the organization of physical files containing documents of various types
Establish or maintain physical files, including proper placement of documents as they are created
Disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
Perform word processing tasks
Perform data entry and metadata entry for electronic documents
Reconcile inconsistencies
Gather information and organize investigative packages, case files, or presentations
Obtain additional information from other investigative agencies or databases
Verify information and files against the tracking system
Maintain internal status information on the disposition of designated information and files
Distribute and receive documents
Assist analyst or government official in obtaining or collecting all documents or information to complete case file
Provide administrative information and assistance concerning the case or files to other agencies or organizations
Other duties as assigned
Qualifications
High school diploma or GED required
Must have resided in the United States for at least three out of the last five years or worked for the U.S. in a foreign country as either an employee or contractor in a federal or military capacity for at least three of the last five years
Valid driver’s license is required
Having your own Personally Owned Vehicle (POV) is required
Top secret clearance required
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:
Possess a demonstrated ability to analyze documents to extract information
Good oral and written communication skills
Have hands-on familiarity with a variety of computer applications, including word processing, database, spreadsheet, and telecommunications software
Must be a team player
Must be able to work independently and with USMS staff to interpret data rapidly and accurately for proper execution in a records management database
Must have a working knowledge of a variety of computer software applications in word processing, spreadsheets, database, presentation software (MS Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint), and Outlook
Ability to work independently on tasks and be a self-starter and complete projects with a team as they arise
Attention to detail and the ability to direct the work of others efficiently and effectively
Ability to consistently deliver high-quality work under extreme pressure
Ability to work shiftwork
Ability to lift and move boxes up to 25 pounds, including frequentlyutilizing hands, arms, and legs for file placement and removal
Experience with scanning software
How you’ll grow
At Chenega MIOS, our professional development plan focuses on helping our team members at every level of their careers to identify and use their strengths to do their best work every day. From entry-level employees to senior leaders, we believe there’s always room to learn.
We offer opportunities to help sharpen skills in addition to hands-on experience in the global, fast-changing business world. From on-the-job learning experiences to formal development programs, our professionals have a variety of opportunities to continue to grow throughout their careers.
Benefits
At Chenega MIOS, we know that great people make a great organization. We value our team members and offer them a broad range of benefits.
Learn more about what working at Chenega MIOS can mean for you.
Chenega MIOS’s culture
Our positive and supportive culture encourages our team members to do their best work every day. We celebrate individuals by recognizing their uniqueness and offering them the flexibility to make daily choices that can help them be healthy, centered, confident, and aware. We offer well-being programs and continuously look for new ways to maintain a culture where we excel and lead healthy, happy lives.
Corporate citizenship
Chenega MIOS is led by a purpose to make an impact that matters. This purpose defines who we are and extends to relationships with our clients, our team members, and our communities. We believe that business has the power to inspire and transform. We focus on education, giving, skill-based volunteerism, and leadership to help drive positive social impact in our communities.
Learn more about Chenega’s impact on the world.
Chenega MIOS News- https://chenegamios.com/news/

description:
About Peraton
Peraton is a next-generation national security company that drives missions of consequence spanning the globe and extending to the farthest reaches of the galaxy. As the world's leading mission capability integrator and transformative enterprise IT provider, we deliver trusted, highly differentiated solutions and technologies to protect our nation and allies. Peraton operates at the critical nexus between traditional and nontraditional threats across all domains: land, sea, space, air, and cyberspace. The company serves as a valued partner to essential government agencies and supports every branch of the U.S. armed forces. Each day, our employees do the can't be done by solving the most daunting challenges facing our customers. Visit peraton.com to learn how we're keeping people around the world safe and secure.
Responsibilities

This is a role is part of a high-impact team delivering critical insights from data to the Sponsor reaching objectives and enabling informed decision making. The Candidate needs to be skilled at gathering, manipulating, and understanding data resources and combines these skills with curiosity and a passion for solving organizational problems. A strong communicator with developed internal client consulting skills, the Candidate will be responsible for understanding the vision and objectives of the Sponsor while proactively finding data-based solutions that lead the organization.

The Data Analyst provides support in visualizing data, providing insights and reports as it relates to various business operations, aggregating data to achieve data-driven insights and results. The Analyst is responsible for measuring and assessing the effectiveness of the data sets. The Data Analytics position deals with issues related to reporting, aggregating, combining multiple internal and external data sources to produce analyses, and metrics.

Duties

Query and mine data resources to answer ad-hoc business questions.
Manipulating Data through visualization in Tableau or other tools
Starting with raw data and a business need or question, deliver high-impact analyses and presentations.
Identify and create new data resources from disparate sources to enable reporting, data science, and advanced analytics.
Understand business objectives and user needs to translate into requirements for reporting, analytics, and data science projects.
Create advanced reporting and dashboards primarily in Tableau and PowerPoint.
Leverage statistical testing and experimental design methodologies to determine impact of organizational actions.
Innovate data science-enabled resources including segmentations and predictive models
Qualifications

Required:

TS/SCI with Polygraph level clearance
BA/BS and 8+ years of experience; Masters and 6+ years of experience; an additional four years of experience may be considered in lieu of degree
Knowledgeable with Tableau and other data visualization tools and techniques
Create and maintain rich interactive visualizations through data interpretation and analysis, with reporting components from multiple data sources
Programming experience with frameworks, including Python & SQL
Must be a self-starter
Ability to translate complex concepts into clear, compelling "stand-alone" graphic products
Ability to manage complex projects and schedules with multiple objectives and priorities
Ability to work collaboratively with a broad range of stakeholders across organizational boundaries to accomplish mission goals
Ability to work under tight deadlines in a fast-paced environment
Desired:

Knowleable with Power BI
Customer domain experience
Benefits:

Peraton offers enhanced benefits to employees working on this critical National Security program, which include heavily subsidized employee benefits coverage for you and your dependents, 25 days of PTO accrued annually up to a generous PTO cap and eligibility to participate in an attractive bonus plan.

Target Salary Range

$135,000 - $216,000. This represents the typical salary range for this position based on experience and other factors.

SCA / Union / Intern Rate or Range

EEO
An Equal Opportunity Employer including Disability/Veteran.

Our Values

Benefits
At Peraton, our benefits are designed to help keep you at your best beyond the work you do with us daily. We're fully committed to the growth of our employees. From fully comprehensive medical plans to tuition reimbursement, tuition assistance, and fertility treatment, we are there to support you all the way.

Paid Time-Off and Holidays
Retirement
Life & Disability Insurance
Career Development
Tuition Assistance and Student Loan Financing
Paid Parental Leave
Additional Benefits
Medical, Dental, & Vision Care

description:
The Claremont Colleges Services (TCCS) is the central coordinating and support organization for a highly regarded cluster of seven independent colleges known as The Claremont Colleges. TCCS, with about 300 staff members, provides exceptional shared services to 9,000 students, and almost 3,600 faculty and staff. TCCS staff work in both student-facing services as well as administrative and operational services. Our numerous departments are located throughout The Claremont Colleges campus in the beautiful city of Claremont, California.

ABOUT THE POSITION :
Purpose: A versatile team member skilled in delivering a wide range of accounting services to The Claremont Colleges Services (TCCS) and The Claremont Colleges (TCC). This role ensures that the internal departments of TCCS receive accurate and timely reports. Responsibilities include budget preparation, general accounting, internal financial reporting, and non-financial data collection. The individual in this position effectively balances independent and collaborative work, handles confidential information with discretion, and is proficient in managing tasks within the Workday system to support TCCS's overall budget model.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

The following are the fundamental duties and responsibilities of this position which the incumbent must be able to perform to fulfill the purpose and requirements of this position.

Accounting

Assists in preparing weekly, monthly, and quarterly journal entries, and is responsible for reviewing journal entries and Supplier Invoices in Workday.

Prepares recurring and ad hoc journal entries and inputs institutional TCCS Supplier Invoices in Workday.

Supports the creation, review, and discussion of monthly Budget to Actual reports for TCCS departments and senior management.

Collaborates closely with the Office of Financial Services to ensure seamless coordination of accounting activities.

Acts as a "superuser" for the financial system, using expertise to develop meaningful reports and provide training to TCCS internal departments. Assists with managing Worktags - keywords or dimensions used in Workday to categorize and describe transactions and events for reporting and security purposes.

Provides customer service by assisting departments with accounting and budget inquiries. Reviews transactions to ensure accurate accounting classification and proper supporting documentation, in line with TCCS policies.

Budget

Assists in the preparation of the annual budget, including setup, data collection, and providing support to directors during budget development, ensuring timeliness and effectiveness of the process.

Provides customer service by assisting departments and intercollegiate programs with budget-related questions.

Data Analysis

Assists management in developing and maintaining organization-wide metrics and data collection processes.

Collects data from TCCS Departments, TCC Colleges, and TCC Programs, ensuring data quality and application accuracy for departments, providing reliable analyses with a high degree of confidence.

Generates recurring metrics reports (monthly, quarterly, annually) for various stakeholders, accurately informing them about the utilization and outcomes of current strategic initiatives.

Produces relevant graphs and charts, drafts narratives for reports to upper management, designs reports to integrate data, and provides regular updates on customer and operational data, with a focus on progress against targets and service level agreements.

QUALIFICATIONS

Education/Training : A bachelor's degree in accounting, business administration, or a related field; or the equivalent in a combination of education, training, and additional work experience beyond the minimum required.

Experience :
At least two (2) years of experience in accounting and financial reporting.

Experience using cloud-based ERP systems is required.

Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:
Proficiency in MS Excel, Word, Outlook, Powerpoint, Teams and Adobe PDF required; strong Microsoft Excel knowledge required.

Foundational understanding of GAAP.

Fundamental understanding of and familiarity with maintaining confidentiality of sensitive information.

Ability to solve problems and work with limited direction

Strong verbal, and written communication in English.

Ability to summarize data in a clear and concise manner and communicate effectively to different stakeholders.

Strong interpersonal skill with the ability to foster collaboration and build positive relationships with internal and external constituencies, including with customers and vendors.

Strong analytical skills with an ability to synthesize and effectively articulate data.

Ability to manage time and assignments to meet expectations and strict deadlines.

Flexibility and comfort adjusting to changing priorities and challenges.

Demonstrate maturity, tact, openness to new ideas and change, resiliency, and composure in difficult and unexpected circumstances.

A service-oriented approach to individuals at all levels and across all disciplines and campuses.

High dedication to professionalism and ethical behavior always at all levels of the organization.

Commitment to always delivering excellent customer services and support.

Able and willing to learn new systems and technologies as needed.

Preferred Qualifications:
Workday experience

Qualtrics experience

Tableau experience

IPEDS knowledge

Experience in business office and administrative support functions.

Experience in Higher Education or other complex organizations

Competencies :
MS Word and Excel proficiency required
Ability to work well with and establish trust with diverse individuals in roles across TCC and TCCS
Organized, acute attention to detail
Strong oral and writing skills
Ability to solve problems and work with limited direction

Work Schedule : The regular hours for this full-time position are [8] hours scheduled from 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday for 12 months annually. May be required to work holiday, weekend, and/or evening hours. Regular hours may vary due to the needs of the organization or business unit. This position is eligible for a hybrid work schedule to work partial hours remotely as approved by the supervisor.

COMPENSATION

Pay : The salary for this position is competitive and commensurate with the duties, responsibilities, and qualifications required for the position, between $70,000 - $80,000 a year depending on experience.

Benefits : This position is eligible for our employment benefits package including:

medical, dental, vision,
10% retirement contributions after one year (no matching required),
group life insurance,
generous time off,
professional development funds,
discounts for mobile plans, software, and entertainment,
access to fitness facilities,
and more!

Disclaimer:
This job description has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to this position. When duties and responsibilities change and develop, The Claremont Colleges Services will review this job description and make changes of business necessity. TCCS reserves the right to modify job duties or assign additional duties as needed.

To view additional information and to apply, visit https://theclaremontcolleges.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/TCCS_Careers/job/Claremont/Junior-Financial-and-Data-Analyst_REQ-6866

Equal Opportunity Employer:
TCCS is an equal opportunity employer. TCCS managers make employment decisions on the basis of merit, with the aim to have the best available person in every job. TCCS prohibits discrimination based on race, color, religious creed (including religious dress and grooming practices), gender (including gender identity and gender expression), national origin or ancestry, genetic information, physical or mental disability, medical condition, marital status, registered domestic partner status, age, sexual orientation, sex (which includes pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, and medical conditions related to pregnancy, childbirth, or breastfeeding), military or veteran status, and status with regard to public assistance, or any other basis protected by federal, state or local law or ordinance or regulation. TCCS also prohibits discrimination based on the perception that anyone has any of these characteristics, or is associated with a person who has or is perceived as having any of these characteristics. title: Data Analyst

description:
Summary:
Job Title: Data Analyst II
FLSA Status: Exempt
Location: Remote
Salary: $105,000 - $125,000

SUMMARY

The Data Analyst II is responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting data related to grant management and project performance. This role involves developing and maintaining dashboards to monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) and providing data-driven insights to support decision-making processes. The Data Analyst II plays a critical role in ensuring data integrity, supporting data management systems, and enhancing the overall data analysis capabilities within the organization. In the absence of a Financial Analyst, the Data Analyst may assume additional responsibilities related to financial data analysis.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

Data Collection and Analysis: Gather, process, and analyze data related to grant management and project performance. Use advanced analytical techniques to interpret complex data sets and provide insights that inform decision-making and strategic planning.
Dashboard Development and Maintenance: Design, develop, and maintain dashboards that track key performance indicators (KPIs) related to grants and project performance. Ensure dashboards are user-friendly, accurate, and provide real-time insights for stakeholders.
Data Management and Quality Assurance: Manage master data, including creation, updates, and deletion. Implement quality assurance protocols to ensure the accuracy and reliability of imported data. Work closely with quality assurance analysts to maintain data integrity.
Reporting and Documentation: Generate detailed analytical reports that summarize data findings, trends, and recommendations. Support the development of training materials and user guides for end-users. Ensure all reports and documentation comply with organizational standards and federal guidelines.
Collaboration and Technical Support: Collaborate with project managers, grant managers, and other stakeholders to support data-driven initiatives. Provide technical expertise on data storage structures, data mining, and data cleansing. Assist with troubleshooting issues related to the reporting database environment.
System Management and Optimization: Manage and design the reporting environment, including data sources, security, and metadata. Support the data warehouse by identifying and revising reporting requirements. Evaluate and implement new software solutions to enhance data analysis capabilities.
Training and User Support: Train end-users on new reports, dashboards, and data management tools. Provide ongoing support and technical assistance to ensure users can effectively utilize data insights for decision-making.
Confidential Data Handling: Ensure all data processing activities comply with federal privacy and confidentiality guidelines. Handle sensitive information with the highest level of security and discretion.
Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS

Proficient in data analysis, data management, and reporting tools.
Experience in developing and maintaining dashboards for tracking KPIs.
Strong knowledge of data integrity, data cleansing, and metadata standards.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets.

description:
Description
ICF is growing, and we are hiring a Food Security Survey Data Analyst to analyze the population-based survey data that is collected from household surveys around the globe. This is a full-time, hybrid position based in Rockville, Maryland.
The Team:
ICF manages the USAID-funded Surveys for Monitoring in Resilience and Food Security (SMRFS) project as part of Feed the Future, the U.S. Government’s flagship initiative to reduce global hunger and improve food security. The SMRFS Team collaborates with local survey implementing organizations to implement population-based surveys (PBS) in targeted geographical areas where the U.S. Government and its partners invest in agriculture, resilience, and nutrition. The SMRFS Team also works with USAID to update and expand Feed the Future’s publicly available population-based survey guidance materials (https://agrilinks.org/search?keywords=ZOI), conduct additional analyses, and investigate ways to reduce burden and collect data using alternative methods.
Once the population-based survey data is collected in a country, the data analysis team cleans and analyzes the data and then summarizes and interprets findings for survey report. In collaboration with the project’s Capacity Strengthening Advisor the data analysis team is responsible for strengthening capacity of USAID mission and implementing partner staff, host country government, and local civil society’s capacity to analyze and use the PBS data once collected. The data analysis team leads ad hoc and in-depth secondary data analysis.
The Work:
As a member of the data analysis team, the food security survey data analyst will work with others to analyze survey data, to interpret findings and write analysis results for survey reports, and to participate in strengthening data analytic capacity in the countries where data is collected.
Key Responsibilities:
Conduct analyses of large survey data sets using statistical software packages
Review the analysis of other staff members
Perform literature reviews
Contribute to writing survey reports
Draft and present findings to diverse audiences
Strengthen data analysis capacity of in-country partners through training and coaching
Assist other project members on non-data analysis activities as needed
Present findings orally and in writing in English
May travel to low- and middle-income countries up to 15% time
Required Qualifications:
Masters degree in economics, statistics, data science, epidemiology, public policy, demography, or related subject
1+ years of experience conducting statistical analysis, including multivariate methods
1+ years of experience using Stata and R
1+ year of experience managing large, population-based survey datasets

Preferred Qualifications:
1+ years of experience working with data collected for international development projects
1+ years of experience applying sample weights to data sets
1 + years of experience working on USAID-funded studies
1+ years of experience in analyzing food security data
Experience presenting to diverse audiences
Written and oral French, Spanish, or Portuguese language skills
Experience using SAS or SPSS or GIS
Working at ICF

Provides data as needed to support internal MCH quality improvement work, within the perinatal care and maternal child health program specialties.

Collaborates with other MCH directors, program managers and staff to gather clinical and programmatic data in support of COH reporting for key grants, including UDS, Healthy Start, Baby & Me, Safe Babies Safe Moms, Optum, Home Visiting, and more, from the perspective of MCH activities.
Collaborates with other members of the Quality Improvement team to produce accurate MCH related data analysis for monthly and quarterly reports for stakeholders such as DC Health and private granters.

Strong organizational skills with an ability to multitask and work with teams.

Experience with Tableau preferred.
Ability to see complex projects through to completion.
Demonstrated cultural competence in communicating with underserved, diverse populations.

Ability to work in a non-profit environment.
At COH, we understand the toll that the Covid-19 pandemic has taken on the workforce, which is why we prioritize the following well-being and work-life balance-centered benefits:
Remote work opportunities are available for many of our roles, promoting a culture of work-life balance.
8-hour workdays, which include a paid lunch
11.5 paid company holidays, 1 personal floating holiday, 15 days of paid vacation (increases to 20 after 3 years of service), and 12 days of paid sick leave on an annual basis

National Health Service Corps (NHSC) and DC Health Professional Loan Repayment Program (DCHPLRP) participants

403(b) Retirement Plan

About Us:
Community of Hope is a mission-driven, innovative, and rapidly growing nonprofit. For over 40 years, we have provided healthcare, housing, and supportive services for under-resourced, underserved and people experiencing homelessness in Washington, DC. As a Federally Qualified Health Center, we provide medical, dental, emotional wellness, and care coordination services for the whole family at three locations in DC. Community of Hope also strongly emphasizes maternal and child health, with midwifery practice and the only free-standing birth center in DC. In 2020, Community of Hope provided about 28,400 medical visits, 7,000 dental visits, and 10,000 behavioral health visits for about 11,000 patients. Community of Hope provides community walk-in COVID testing and COVID vaccines. Community of Hope is also one of the largest providers in DC of housing and support services for families and individuals experiencing homelessness. Through providing these programs, we live out our mission to improve health and end family and individual homelessness to make Washington, DC, more equitable.
We were selected as one of The Washington Post 150 Top Workplaces in 2024 and 6 other times since 2014 based on feedback from our staff.

description:
Weaver is seeking an Inventory / Data Analyst. In this position you will complete and conduct analysis of inventory levels to ensure efficient operations, minimize costs and meet customer demands.
The job responsibilities of this position include, but are not limited to the following:
Analyze historical sales data and trends to determine what current inventory levels should be.
Understand and recommend appropriate inventory levels based on turn rates, # of customers, Volatility (Safety Stock), historical out of stock rates, prioritized customers, as well as orders we were not able to fill due to not having inventory.
Evaluate & validate data to ensure accuracy.
Present data and identify potential opportunities for corresponding inventory actions to Purchasing and Operations Management.
Build models that show inventory valuation by fill rate, service levels, and by ABC code including lead time/MOQ’s, etc.
Give clarity on the impact of adjusting service levels and how it affects inventory amounts & dollars.
Give inventory level prediction based on forecast accuracy (if demand does not match forecast how will this affect inventory?).
Evaluate large customers (Amazon, TSC etc.) order history and demand forecast.
Participate in demand planning meetings to help make recommendations based on reasoning/justifications.
Help develop new product forecasts.
Identify products to recommend for deletion.
Develop and/or maintain a system to benchmark purchased items with regular review.
Track resourcing and cost negotiations with vendors.
Participate in make vs buy reviews and make recommendations on best course of action.
Other related duties as assigned by management.
Our ideal applicant:
Bachelor’s degree in data analytics, business administration, finance, or related field.
Minimum of one year of experience in inventory management, data analysis, or a similar role.
Understanding of statistical analysis and forecasting techniques.
Knowledge of supply chain and logistics process.
Strong interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Self-starter with a high degree of integrity and initiative.
Detail oriented, flexible in style and approach, and able to prioritize multiple projects under tight deadlines.
Proficient in Microsoft Excel, SQL, Power BI, and other inventory management software
We offer a competitive wage and benefit package as well as a terrific, team-oriented work environment.

Eccalon, LLC is looking for a Senior Data Analyst to support the Department of Defense?s (DOD) Office of Small Business Programs (OSBP). OSBP is responsible for the development of small business policy, oversight of DoD's small business performance for prime and subcontracting goals, administration of small business programs, industry engagement, ensuring cyber resiliency of the small business industrial base and utilization of technology and big data principles to drive market research and small business inclusion in defense procurements.
The Senior Data Analyst will provide with subject matter expertise in the overall management and performance of small business data analytics. OSBP is responsible for the analysis of federal procurement data to track small business performance towards statutory goals and to look for industries, and sectors for small business performance improvement. This includes policies and procedures for small business performance management across the DoD, supporting the establishment of small business goals for the defense agencies, utilizing tools and technologies for performance management and data analysis of small business contracting information for prime and sub-contract awards. description:
About DMI:
DMI is a leading global provider of digital services working at the intersection of public and private sectors. With broad capabilities across IT managed services, cybersecurity, cloud migration and application development, DMI provides on-site and remote support to clients within governments, healthcare, financial services, transportation, manufacturing, and other critical infrastructure sectors. DMI has grown to over 2,100+ employees globally and has been continually recognized as a Top Workplace in both regional and national categories.
About the Opportunity:
At DMI, we are seeking a passionate and detail-oriented Data Analyst to join our Technical Services team. This role will sit onsite in our Cincinnati office. In this role, you will be at the forefront of leveraging data to drive business decisions, working closely with cross-functional teams to provide actionable insights. As part of our data-centric culture, you will use Domo to develop visually compelling dashboards and reports, transforming complex data sets into clear and impactful visualizations. Your work will empower leaders across the organization to make data-driven decisions that shape the future of our services and products.

With at least two years of hands-on experience using Domo, you will play a key role in identifying trends and patterns from large data sets, translating them into meaningful recommendations for our business units. Collaborating with both technical and non-technical stakeholders, you will ensure data accuracy and develop a deep understanding of our business needs. Your ability to interpret complex data and effectively communicate your findings will contribute to guiding key strategic initiatives at DMI.

DMI creates an environment where innovation thrives, and we are looking for a Data Analyst who shares that passion. You will have the opportunity to work on diverse data projects, pushing the boundaries of what data can do for our business. As you grow with us, you'll have a direct impact on DMI's data strategy, contributing to a culture of continuous improvement and excellence in data analytics.

Duties and Responsibilities:
Design and Develop Dashboards: Create dynamic, visually engaging dashboards and reports in Domo that provide real-time insights to stakeholders across various departments, ensuring data is actionable and easy to interpret.
Data Extraction and Transformation: Extract data from multiple sources, transform it into usable formats, and ensure its consistency, accuracy, and reliability for analytical purposes.
Advanced Data Analysis: Conduct detailed analysis on large datasets, utilizing statistical techniques to identify trends, patterns, and correlations that inform key business decisions.
Stakeholder Collaboration: Partner with cross-functional teams, including sales, marketing, and operations, to gather business requirements and translate them into analytical queries that drive decision-making.
Report Automation: Build automated reporting tools that provide stakeholders with timely access to key performance indicators (KPIs) and other relevant metrics, ensuring the business stays informed on critical developments.
Data Quality Assurance: Implement and monitor data validation processes to ensure the integrity of the data used in analysis, including identifying and correcting inconsistencies and errors.
Predictive Analytics: Develop predictive models to forecast business outcomes and customer behaviors, helping the company anticipate changes and make proactive adjustments to strategies.
Documentation and Training: Maintain detailed documentation of data workflows, methodologies, and dashboards. Provide training and support to team members and stakeholders on how to utilize data tools and interpret reports effectively.
Performance Monitoring: Track and analyze the performance of various business service delivery functions, providing insights and recommendations for process improvements, operational efficiencies, and revenue growth opportunities.
Ad Hoc Analysis: Respond to requests for custom data analysis and reporting, working closely with senior leadership to provide insights that address specific business challenges or strategic initiatives
Qualifications:
Education and Years of Experience:
Bachelor’s Degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field is required.
Advanced degrees such as a Master’s in Data Analytics or Business Intelligence are preferred but not mandatory.
2+ years of hands-on experience working with Domo for data visualization and analytics is preferred but not mandatory.
At least 2 years of experience with data analysis, SQL querying, and data reporting.
Familiarity with other data visualization tools like Tableau or Power BI is a plus.
Experience working with large datasets and conducting statistical analysis.
Required and Desired Skills/Certifications:
Domo: Advanced knowledge and hands-on experience with Domo for data visualization, dashboard creation, and analytics.
SQL: Strong proficiency in SQL to query databases, manipulate large datasets, and perform complex data joins and aggregations.
Excel: Advanced skills in Excel, including experience with formulas, pivot tables, and data analysis tools.
Data Warehousing & ETL: Experience with data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) processes to ensure data accuracy and consistency.
Data Visualization: Ability to create impactful data visualizations and reports using tools like Power BI or Tableau, in addition to Domo.
Statistical Analysis: Strong foundation in statistical methods and models to perform predictive analytics, trend analysis, and correlation analysis.
Programming: Familiarity with programming languages such as Python or R for data manipulation and analysis is a plus.
Data Quality Management: Skills in ensuring data quality, accuracy, and consistency through validation checks and error identification.
Analytical Thinking: Ability to analyze complex datasets, draw meaningful insights, and recommend data-driven solutions.
Communication: Excellent verbal and written communication skills to present insights effectively to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Problem Solving: Strong problem-solving abilities, with a focus on using data to address business challenges and identify growth opportunities.
Attention to Detail: High attention to detail, ensuring that all analyses and reports are accurate and error-free.
Additional Requirements:
Prolonged Sitting: Must be able to sit for long periods while working at a computer workstation.
Repetitive Motions: Frequent repetitive movements such as typing on a keyboard and using a mouse.
Visual Focus: Ability to consistently focus on a computer screen for extended periods, with good near-vision capabilities.
Occasional Lifting: May need to lift objects such as laptops, documents, or small office equipment, usually weighing under 20 lbs.
Mobility: Able to move within an office environment, including attending meetings, and collaborating with team members.
Speaking and Listening: Clear verbal communication is essential, as is the ability to hear and understand instructions during meetings.
Manual Dexterity: Capable of handling office equipment and devices requiring fine motor skills (e.g., computer peripherals).
Mental Focus: Prolonged periods of concentration required for data analysis, error-checking, and report creation.
Frequent Typing: The job demands consistent and precise typing for inputting data, writing reports, and generating emails. Speed and accuracy in typing are crucial as it directly impacts productivity and data integrity.
Ability to Work in an Office Environment: Must be able to work a standard 40-hour week in a professional office setting. This includes the capability to commute reliably to and from the office, whether via personal or public transportation. Occasional overtime may be required based on project deadlines or business needs.
Min Citizenship Status Required: Must be a U.S. Citizen
Location: this position sits onsite in Cincinnati, OH

Working at DMI
DMI is a diverse, prosperous, and rewarding place to work. Being part of the DMI family means we care about your wellbeing. We offer a variety of perks and benefits that help meet various interests and needs, while still having the opportunity to work directly with several of our award-winning, Fortune 1000 clients. The following categories make up your DMI wellbeing:
Convenience/Concierge - Virtual visits through health insurance, pet insurance, commuter benefits, discount tickets for movies, travel, and many other items to provide convenience.
Development – Annual performance management, continuing education, and tuition assistance, internal job opportunities along with career enrichment and advancement to help each employee with their professional and personal development.
Financial – Generous 401k matches both pre-tax and post-tax (ROTH) contributions along with financial wellness education, EAP, Life Insurance and Disability help provide financial stability for each DMI employee.
Recognition – Great achievements do not go unnoticed by DMI through Annual Awards ceremony, service anniversaries, peer-to-peer acknowledgment, employee referral bonuses.
Wellness – Healthcare benefits, Wellness programs, Flu Shots, Biometric screenings, and several other wellness options.
Employees are valued for their talents and contributions. We all take pride in helping our customers achieve their goals, which in turn contributes to the overall success of the company. The company does and will take affirmative action to employ and advance in employment individuals with disabilities and protected veterans, and to treat qualified individuals without discrimination based on their physical or mental disability or veteran status. DMI is an Equal Opportunity Employer Minority/Female/Veterans/Disability. DMI maintains a drug-free workplace.

description:
Full Performance Data Analyst
The Opportunity:
As a data analyst, you love diving into data and turning it into meaningful insights. With the abundance of structured and unstructured data, you understand the importance of transforming complex data sets into useful information to solve challenges. As a data analyst at Booz Allen, you can use your skills and experience to support a mission and use data for good. We need a data expert like you to bring your expertise to measure our client's performance and effectiveness.
As a client-facing data analyst on our National Security team, you’ll work closely with your clients to understand their questions and needs and then dig into their data-rich environments to find the pieces of their information puzzle. Not only will you provide a deep understanding of their data, but you’ll also advise your client on what the information means and how it can be used to make an impact on Intelligence production and drive insights by telling the data story.
How You’ll Contribute:
As a data analyst on our team, you’ll:
Use your data analytics expertise to support client and stakeholder relationships.
Research, develop, and test data methodologies, and generate cross-functional solutions through the collection, interpretation, evaluation, and analysis of large data sets.
Contribute to impactful work and guide decision-making across multiple organizations.
Apply consulting skills and data analytics expertise by simplifying technical requirements and trends, based on audience.
Present data findings and recommendations to clients and stakeholders.
Establish quantitative and qualitative metrics and key performance indicators to drive technical outcomes.
Apply data visualization through different formats such as graphs, tables, and PowerPoint slides.
Contextualize data to address stakeholder questions.
Develop user-friendly, easy-to-understand visualizations for customers to meet business and mission needs.
Create, enhance, and maintain data visualizations using Tableau.
Develop interpretive statements and assertions based on analyses, available information, and data holdings.
Work with us to drive large-scale business and process decisions through data insights.
Join us. The world can’t wait.
You Have:
Experience with using SQL to ingest data sets
Experience with using Tableau to create dashboards and visualizations
Experience with IC collection reporting
Experience with developing data standards or operating data governance efforts within and across IC elements
Experience with evaluating and monitoring data quality using database tools and data visualization techniques
Experience with developing data standards or interface documentation as implemented in an international, IC, or government specification, including ICPUBS or NITF
Experience with implementing software tools and associated processes for data governance and specification, including Collibra or Alation
Knowledge of databases and scripting languages, including SQL, Python, and Microsoft Office Suite
TS/SCI clearance with a polygraph
Bachelor’s degree in Business Information Systems or Library Science
Clearance:
Applicants selected will be subject to a security investigation and may need to meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information; TS/SCI clearance with polygraph is required.
Compensation
At Booz Allen, we celebrate your contributions, provide you with opportunities and choices, and support your total well-being. Our offerings include health, life, disability, financial, and retirement benefits, as well as paid leave, professional development, tuition assistance, work-life programs, and dependent care. Our recognition awards program acknowledges employees for exceptional performance and superior demonstration of our values. Full-time and part-time employees working at least 20 hours a week on a regular basis are eligible to participate in Booz Allen’s benefit programs. Individuals that do not meet the threshold are only eligible for select offerings, not inclusive of health benefits. We encourage you to learn more about our total benefits by visiting the Resource page on our Careers site and reviewing Our Employee Benefits page.
Salary at Booz Allen is determined by various factors, including but not limited to location, the individual’s particular combination of education, knowledge, skills, competencies, and experience, as well as contract-specific affordability and organizational requirements. The projected compensation range for this position is $75,600.00 to $172,000.00 (annualized USD). The estimate displayed represents the typical salary range for this position and is just one component of Booz Allen’s total compensation package for employees. This posting will close within 90 days from the Posting Date.
Work Model
Our people-first culture prioritizes the benefits of flexibility and collaboration, whether that happens in person or remotely.
If this position is listed as remote or hybrid, you’ll periodically work from a Booz Allen or client site facility.
If this position is listed as onsite, you’ll work with colleagues and clients in person, as needed for the specific role.
EEO Commitment
We’re an equal employment opportunity/affirmative action employer that empowers our people to fearlessly drive change – no matter their race, color, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, lactation, or related medical conditions), national origin, ancestry, age, marital status, sexual orientation, gender identity and expression, disability, veteran status, military or uniformed service member status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable federal, state, local, or international law.

description:
The ESG Data Specialist will serve to support the organizations rapidly evolving ESG data needs. The candidate will serve as the organizations primary lead in ESG data collection efforts, leading data-focused projects, and interfacing across various functions. The role is highly collaborative, working with our various teams to collect relevant ESG data, maintain data storage, assess database design, and gather, organize, and interpret relevant statistical information.
JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:
Manages all aspects of the of the ESG data collection process including setting deadlines, assigning responsibilities, and monitoring, expediting, summarizing, and communicating progress at regular intervals to ensure the organization meets it annual ESG reporting deadlines.
Identifies and addresses limitations of ESG data.
Aggregates ESG data as necessary to support organizations sustainability reporting.
Understands our evolving ESG data needs, how our current data meets those needs; identifies, evaluates, and recommends complementary data sets.
Analyze existing ESG data sources and methodologies for accuracy.
Contributes to the development of dashboards or Power BI’s to improve ESG process integration where applicable.
Recommends ands supports implementation of data solutions for evolving external reporting needs, including regulatory requirements.
Ensures that data collection, analysis and reporting projects are completed on time and within estimated costs.

description:
Product & Regulatory Operations (PRO) plays a critical role in product development and legal compliance at Meta. They provide data and insights to build and improve products, like Facebook, Instagram, and Reality Labs.As a horizontal analytics team, Product & Regulatory Operations Analytics enables teams across PRO to make data-informed decisions by serving as analytics thought-partners to solve operational business problems. We build foundational data products and employ a diverse toolkit of analytical approaches to guide decision making.In this role, you won’t simply present data, but tell data-driven stories and share actionable insights. You will influence operations and systems using clear insights and recommendations, develop data-driven investment strategies to optimize product outcomes, and collaborate with a diverse set of cross-functional partners to identify, quantify, and solve PRO’s biggest challenges.This work utilizes one of the largest data sets in the world and drives high-stakes outcomes that impact billions of people on and off the platform. By joining Meta, you will become part of a world-class analytics community dedicated to skill development and career growth in analytics and beyond.


Data Analyst, Product & Regulatory Ops Responsibilities:
Identify metric trends and insights for business reviews to provide leadership visibility into operational health and performance against desired outcomes
Translate business objectives into actionable analyses, clearly communicating technical concepts and operational implications to varied audiences
Develop scalable analytics solutions that provide the essential insights needed to support agile decision making
Apply quantitative skills and incorporate qualitative insights to inform and influence strategy for Product Delivery Operations
Partner with Operations, Data Science, Data Engineering, Systems, and Engineering teams to identify and execute against opportunities that increase operational efficiency and effectiveness
Drive forecasting, scenario planning, and predictive analytics to optimize our operational expenditures



Minimum Qualifications:
B.A./B.S. degree with a quantitative focus in Economics, Computer Science, Information Systems, Math, Statistics, or a similar technical field
5+ years of work experience in an analytics or consulting role involving strategy, problem solving, and/or technical systems
Experience working in a fast-paced, rapidly-changing environment, while managing multiple priorities and stakeholders
Experience communicating effectively to technical and non-technical audiences
Experience in communication with senior management
Experience using analytics to break down ambiguous, complex problems using data
Experience with data querying languages (e.g. SQL) and experience with scripting languages (e.g. Python)



Preferred Qualifications:
Experience developing data pipelines via SQL and Python-based ETL frameworks
Experience working in an operations organization
Advanced degree with a quantitative focus (Computer Science, Statistics, Finance, Information Systems, Applied Economics or similar technical field) or equivalent practical experience

Meta builds technologies that help people connect, find communities, and grow businesses. When Facebook launched in 2004, it changed the way people connect. The Department of Health Care Services (DHCS) is the backbone of California’s health care safety net. Our success is made possible by the hard work of more than 4,800 DHCS team members and through collaboration with the federal government and other state agencies, counties, and partners for the care of low-income families, children, pregnant women, older adults, and persons with disabilities. This is an exciting opportunity to join our diverse team in the following role. If you are interested in joining our team, apply today!

About this Role:

The Research Data Analyst II (RDA II), under the general direction of the Chief, LLAU, performs a variety of tasks including the more independent, responsible, varied and complex technical research and data analysis in support of the litigation and legislative processes for the CA-MMIS Division. The incumbent independently develops and employs sophisticated research methodology and techniques using a variety of data and research sources, designs and implements research projects, and may act as lead on research projects. The incumbent will also perform the more complex data retrieval of Medi-Cal claims and eligibility files, fee-for-service encounter data, and using in-depth analysis to ensure that responses to cases brought against the Department comply with all applicable laws, rules, regulations and policies that govern the Medi-Cal program and assist in correcting any programmatic issues.

DHCS is a dynamic organization with ambitious goals and talented, committed employees. We work hard every day to fulfill our vital responsibility to support the delivery of quality health care to Californians. DHCS is committed to addressing disparities within our organization and communities through efforts toward greater diversity, equity, and inclusion. This is accomplished, in part, by a commitment toward employing a diverse workforce that reflects the many communities we serve, and by promoting and enforcing equal employment opportunity.

Take a look at some of DHCS' recent projects and happenings that our Department has accomplished in the DHCS Newsroom.

The California Medicaid Information System (CA-MMIS) Operations Division is responsible for oversight of the Medi-Cal Fiscal Intermediary (FI) contractors, who provide Business Operations and Information Technology Maintenance and Operations services. CA-MMIS is a large, highly automated, complex, and interrelated data processing system, which depends on the operation of a large data center by the FI contractor. The CA-MMIS is a mission-critical system to the Department of Health Care Services (DHCS) and the State of California. This system annually processes and adjudicates medical claims that result in approximately $22 billion annually in payments to health care providers.

The CA-MMIS Operations Division is located on Stillwater Road in West Sacramento.
